\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid16391728 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs20\insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Could you give me your name and address please?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 That's - Carline Bessie Costello. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}27 Lamps Court
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Bethwin Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, S.E.5. Camberwell.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 And your year of marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 1919.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Could you tell me your year of birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 1893. In the Old Kent Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How many years did you live in the house you were born in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 That I don't know. In those days you could walk out of one place into another. How long they lived in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Leroy Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, that was in the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Old Kent Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, I do not know. I do know my father was working on Tower Bridge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you move house several times in your childhood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes.
 Well - not far, but we did, you know. We didn't do - we didn't jump the gun or anything like that, but we just - you had one up and one down, then you took two up - two up you know two down. Practically in the same place, Weston Street Bermondsey, and fr
o
m there we went to Kipling Street Bermondsey, still all round that way and - we had one of Guys houses, we had one of those for a long long time. Father was in and out of work then and - the collector was wonderfully good to my mother, very good - out of 
the Counting House at Guys. Father had been out of work and mother told him this time she said, Charlie's made a mistake - made a start or {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Warwick{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, I don't know which she said. And - he said, all right, make a fresh start. Tore the book in half, so she had a fresh start there. He was very good to her. And we were there then - until after the war - towards the end of the first war. And then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 About what age did you go there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well, I should - I was there while I was still at school anyway, in that G
uys house because mother had - had - how I remember that mostly, my mother had a very very bad dose of - infection - skin disease, I can't remember, it'll come to me while I'm talking and - the land - the collector wanted to get her into Guys, the doctor 
wouldn't let her go. "Course I was off from school. He said, do you want your mother to go away? I said, no, she's all right. He said, yes, she is all right. Let her stop. So that suited me and suited}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1996598\charrsid13588098  him. And - mother got erysipela}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 s. It - it wasn't so much
 infection, it was brought on through - the blows or something like that, it - you know, you didn't - she didn't have to go away because it was infectious.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Was there anything special about these Guys houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no, they were very very old fashi
oned, they're all down now. My mother played up for a copper to boil her clothes in, and - he said, well yes, you can have it Mrs Warwick but it'll be another sixpence on the rent. She said, sixpence to do me own washing? Don't you mention it. But however
 she got it. And - they always used to come in and do the decorating very very quick. They were very good to my mother. Yes, quite good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Do you think they were good to all their tenants or particularly to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well, my mother I think she 
was fairly honest - in those days and, she was like me, she could meet people half way, talk to them, and they would meet her you know. She didn't very often sort of ruck anybody, unless they deserved it and then they - she could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 She was straight with people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Oh yes, very straight my mother was. She never - what we used to call at those days, let anybody take it out of the knocker. She wasn't going to pay the rent she'd open it and say, well, sorry, can't be done. Same with everybody else and th
ey - took it didn't they, had to. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 And she'd pay them when she could?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Mrs Costello has told me that she was born in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}
Leroy Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Old Kent Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. Then in about 1895, she's not exactly share of the year, she moved to Gu
iness Buildings. And in 1898 or there abouts she moved to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Kipling Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, Long Lane, Bermondsey, and in 1905 to Snows Fields.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 That's Bermondsey. That's - that's - just across the park.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You stayed there 'til 1919 when you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No. 
No, not 1919. Must have been 1918 I should think nearer, I was married in 1919 but by that time we were at - Flint Street, Walworth. About 1918, all through the Zeppelin raids and that we were in Snowsfields. Right the end of the war, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Where did you go to from Snowsfields?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Flint Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. Walworth. Yes. Got that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Do you remember why the family made these moves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well I think to get bigger places, different landlords, and I know in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Kipling Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} we lived upstairs and the landlady mov
ed and left us in the house. And what happened then of course I mean - mothers didn't tell you every move on the board - and from there we went to Kipling - to Snowsfields. But whether it was over the landlady moving or what happened I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What was your father's occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
He was what they called a hammerman in the - blacksmith. Blacksmith's hammerman. He wasn't a farrier, he worked on railings and - wheels - wheelwright, in a wheelwright's shop and all that sort of thing, he done riveting on - on 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Tower{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Bridge{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. 'Cos that's all -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Do you know whether he ever did any other sort of work before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, he was - trained to be a rivetter. For }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1996598\charrsid13588098 boiler making}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 . And then - he's like my boys, he grew afterwards. Mine were very tine until 
they left school and then up they went. And he done the same. But - when he used to be out of work - he used to pull all the boilers belonging to the churches all the way round and they said that they never had one that could take a boiler to pieces like 
he could. Of course he'd served his time at it. And they get inside to do the riveting - so I'm told. I don't know. But he got too tall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did he do any other sort of part time or casual work do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well - I don't think he was too fussy if he was out of work but I don't know that there was much else going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 But you had the impression he'd take anything to tide him over?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes, he did. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Do you remember your father being out of work at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. He was more o
ften out than in. And my mother - I'm going to tell you something - now that is the truth. When he was doing casual work, done a day's work, he'd take her straight in his money. She was better off with him out of work than she was with him in work. 'Cos w
hen he got a handful he had a few drinks before he come home. See? Yes, she - she never minded him being out of work and we - well, never minded, she did, but we never went without. He always saw that we got something.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 So when he was out of work it'd be a matter of a day here and there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Yes. Yes. Rather than weeks on end. He used to do quite a lot at Waygood's, the lift people. Was a good workman there but they didn't pay very much money, so if he heard of another job going he'd turn that it and 
go somewhere else. Then when he was out again he'd go back there. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 This sort of work even today is still fairly casual?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You were saying that you wouldn't move outside of the Borough of Bermondsey?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well you couldn't, as I
 say, he used to get the casual work on the Bermondsey Vestry. Sometimes he'd do the sweeping and that sort of thing, but it was all on Bermondsey Vestry. You more or less had to stay where you were known, you know, to get the - casual work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Do you know where your father came from originally? Was he a Londoner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Oh, a Londoner. His brother - of course I don't know anything about his father, but I think they all came from round Southwark, all round - of course there was all boilershops and all that
 all round Southwark, round Bankside way. But his brother bought his house from the Woolwich Co-op at - he lived at Plumstead, his eldest brother. 'Course there was a bit of grievance there wasn't there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Do you know how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 He was a lot older than mother but I can't tell you exactly. No, I don't know.-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 There was three of us - alive, but mother lost a lot of babies. Quite a few. She lost four or five after my sister was born.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Where do you come?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I was - in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Leroy Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, Bermondsey of course - what do you mean. I'm the oldest. Yes. The one next to me died with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1996598\charrsid13588098 diphtheria}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
 in Guiness' buildings. Then there's Harry. He's five years younger than me. That's his wife. And seven between me and Emma.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did any of the children, the other children your mother had live until they were a year old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes, yes, she had - well the one that died with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1996598\charrsid13588098 diphtheria}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098  was two. And they were all round about from si
x months to just over a year, I can't tell you. I've got all the certificates but not death certificates. I offered them to Harry but he said, no, you keep 'em, so there there as far as I know, I don't think anybody - but my youngest one'd dig you out of 
his grave if he wanted to know anything so they may not be there but I expect they are.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Was your mother a local {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 woman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes, yes, she come from Bankside. You know, Southwark.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did she have any jobs before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 She had 
the one job all her life, even after - after she was married, I don't know exactly what went wrong, but I know it was something to do with the church visitor. We lived upstairs in the house then in Long Lane and - she'd been talking to this woman downstai
r
s, my mother owed some rent then, and - this woman told this lady that mother had got a job in her hands. And she flies upstairs. Mrs Warwick, you could go to work. She said, yes, I know I could go to work. Do you want to go back to work with no wedding r
i
ng on your finger? Girls you've worked with all your life. Oh poverty's no disgrace. So of course mother goes to work. She worked ever since. Worked until she couldn't work any longer. She was a boxmaker down at - Bankside again, and - stitched cardboard 
b
oxes with ordinary needle and thread. Eight in the morning 'til eight at night, as she told this woman, she said, pay her to mind me baby, pay her to do me washing, she said, I'll have nothing left, but that's all right I'll go to work. 'Course she was in
 the company wasn't she, she was glad to get out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What was this church visitor doing then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Mission{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 hall I think. She was a Miss Cotterell. Very very tiny, very ototty. While this row was going on - my mother told her, she said, they call you the 
ferret. Now, she said, go and find out - he's told you he only earns a guinea a week, go up to Hardings and find out what he does earn and, she said, and when you're down there pull the corks out of the medicine bottles. Oh, she said, Mrs Warwick, you are
 in a temper. She said, I know I am, but it's the truth. She went back and apologized. Oh yes, she went back and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1996598\charrsid13588098 apologised}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
. I mean, when you get us cornered, you get it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did this church visitor used to come round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well now and again, just to - well, just - visiting. They lived in - there was a lot of them lived in - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Trinity Square{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, off the Borough there, there was a lot of them about, and she used to come quite often, this Miss Cotterell. She only took a two I think it was in a shoe and my mother could - was the only one that could wear her shoes so mother used to get her shoes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Your mother said about going back without her wedding ring?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Well she'd pawned it you see. Yes. Well you - well you do, you don't have rings on your finger
s when you want - something else you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did she continue this work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Yes. Right through - not in the second world - no, wait a minute, yes, yes, she went - they didn't get any pay when they were first apprenticed to this job you know, they wor
ked so many weeks for nothing, then they only had a little. And then she worked right through - was it the first war or the second. Must have been this - must have been the first. Hers came under luxuries. So she was out of work. And I was at work, my sis
t
er of course five years younger, she couldn't get a job because she was under eighteen, I'd got a job on munitions. And we weren't supposed to go from one lot of munitions to another. But I was determined I'd go down the Arsenal. My father said, you're no
t
 going. I did. - I got there. And of course I'd got labour cards, that was the first time we paid labour money, I suppose you've heard this. Yes. It was the first time we paid labour money and you couldn't go from one lot of munitions, I was working on ga
s
 masks, couldn't go from there to go down to Woolwich Arsenal on another lot - of munitions, you'd be out of work for six weeks while you were - however I done it without any - gave a previous reference, and done it. My sister couldn't get a job. So I sai
d
, now look Emma, there's my cards, we were paid every night, I said, go in with my cards, it's the same name, same address, it was only our Christian names. So Emma went in with my cards. I go to work down the Arsenal. Mother's work comes under luxuries s
o
 she couldn't get anything, but she did get - I think that was the first start of working for - Smith's Crisps. They made them in a little house the back of the Old Bailey and they fried the crisps in a copper that we - would have washed clothes in. And t
h
at's - and they rubbed them down with a sort of a knife on their hands on a - the potatoes. 'Cos when mother went up the Labour Exchange for a job they asked her could she cook potatoes, she said, well I've brought a family up, I should be able to. And th
at's what they sent her to do, and she done that for quite a long time while the war was on, the first war. As I say, I was down the Arsenal. We used to have the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1996598\charrsid13588098 zeppelins}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 , not very often but we did have them. As soon as we had a warning I used to come home
. They'd say, - where are you going? Oh I've only got one mother. Come home. Make a pot of tea and - find them and that was that. I never saw any fear. Nor I didn't in this last war. Yes. It's - it's - you know, you can't account for it, people don't beli
eve you, but it's the truth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Who looked after you children while your mother was working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well as I say, we talk about - key children now. But we were done just the same. We done just the same. - Only - we were left our jobs to do indoors, we had
 to go straight from school, go in, get your errands, do what work was allocated to you and God help you if you didn't do it, but otherwise - we were just - I had a - I don't know if you - I don't suppose you do, Miss Patmore, she's on her holidays now, s
he does a lot of welfare work, I was talking to her like I am to you now, she said, we were just as much key children, she said, my mother went to work and left us. In those days, they had to.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Which of these addresses do you-remember best while you were still at school? Which is the one you spent longest in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Be Snowsfields. And Guys houses. We had two there. Yes. Yes. We had two houses there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Could you tell me how many rooms there were in the house at Snowsfields?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 In the first one there was one up and one down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 This is Snowsfield?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Yes. And then across the road there was two down, two up. That's why we moved over you see. Not on much more ground, only that they were divided.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Which one did you spend longest in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well 
I should think the second one, I don't - yes. Well there's not much to it really, I mean I was - I was at service then most of the time that I only went home once a week or so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Could we talk about {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Kipling Street{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Go on, what do you want to know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How many rooms were there in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I think there was six but we only had about three upstairs. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did anyone else besides your parents and brothers and sisters live in these three rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no, not with us. No. No, my father wouldn't have anything like that. Not even when they came up from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
country-region}}Wales{\*\xmlclose}, granny had some friends, she used to come up from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Wales{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 but father would not put them up. No, he wouldn't have them in his place. Oh no, he was very much for - morals and law and order you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no. No, we had to get on with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Was the washing done at home or sent out?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Mostly at home, although we used to meet her Saturday dinner time, she used to take it i
nto the baths and do it. We used to take it up and meet her when she came home at - when she left off work at Saturdays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What about your clothes, were these new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well I - mother had a shop that she used to go and pay weekly. And th
ey got to know her, and if anything was there that they thought would suit her - they put it to one side. I think we mostly had new at the start, I don't say - and father used to get off the same shop, there was Layman's in the Borough, a big second - wel
l
 sort of second hand but they done a lot of misfits. And father used to get his clothes there, he used to get beautiful clothes he did - there. He used to go in for the grey - striped trousers and waistcoats and black jackets. He was always - better dress
ed than the average but - he was gifted with it, you know what I mean, he paid for it and he was gifted to - know what suited him, and I think mother was with us children, we were always tidy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did your mother make any of the family clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Not a
 lot. Not a lot. She worked with - needle in thread, but it was big you know, she didn't do a lot, granny done a lot of repairs for us. She was very good she was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about shoes, were these new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no, new. And he was very fussy w
ith shoes too, we weren't allowed to have high heels, they had to be just so to suit Lord Muck. I remember he gave us a right roasting one day, my sister and I, we'd got high legged boots. 'Cos they used to be like kid gloves then. I had grey, she had blu
e. We met him when he was drunk. Oh - did he go for us over our high legged boots.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Was this because he didn't like fashion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I think he was just in the mood, I don't know. Might have been. Perhaps they were a bit too posh for him, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Was there any special time for buying clothes, or just as you needed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well I think mostly holiday times. Easter if possible for the summer, and then again like at Christmastime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did your father help in the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes, when he was out of work he saw to things. He'd - you know, get a meal ready and - look round and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 He'd wash up and things like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes. Didn't suit the old girl but still, he'd do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about decorating and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Not a lot. Not a lot of decorating, he has done it, but of course - you couldn't suit mother with things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about the younger children, would he have anything to do with them when they were young, would he bath them or dress them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
I don't know about bathing and dressing but he would look after them, nurse them, make a fuss of them, and even our children, he was very good with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 And he did look after them when your mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Oh yes. Oh yes. And we always 
- this is one thing that he always did see to, we always had a fire guard. Not a word - he was not quite as long as you but he used to sit one side with his feet right across it. She used to rave over that. But still - that was that. But we always had a f
i
reguard, always fussy with things like that. He really was with a lot. He was good you know. I think it had been - born in him. 'Cos they were both - above our own - that we were mixing with you know, they were both better educated, they could both read a
n
d write and understand, I think even mother's father - and that's going back a few years, could read. 'Cos I've heard mother say when they lived in the Court down Bankside - her father used to have Lloyds News and read to the neighbours. But - I mean it's
 
sort of brought - born in us that we're not - I'm not being proud or anything like that, but you understand don't you. Yes. That's right, yes. Yes, yes. And one thing I do remember that you never hear these days, people don't believe it, my father never w
e
nt up the stairs at night without calling out if we were all right. He never came up - unless we were all - covered and etcetera you know. Yes, that's one thing that's sort of in us you know. But I think that a lot of this immorality, if you start - from 
babies it's there, you can't help it.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 These things are ingrained from childhood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes, and even before then really and truly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What sort of tasks did you have to do in the house to help your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh, wash up and scrub and clean. Fath
er always done windows. He always done windows and boots, but we had to do the clearing and washing up see, she'd take a cup and if it wasn't just so round there you'd get a backhander. And the washing up had to be done just so.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you have regular weekly tasks, did you have one set of things to do and your sister something else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Oh - oh I think we - well of course she was the youngest and we were brought up that we had to give in to the youngest, but - the actual - cleaning right through from top to bottom I think was mostly done the weekend, Friday nights and Saturdays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about your brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Oh yes, he had to do the fireplace. Come home from the first world war and stood with his uniform on him and went for us. We had an open rang
e and he used to take it all to pieces out in the yard and polish - take the oven doors off and all what - and while he was away - he used to whiten the hearth, there was a black fender, you know, the usual, and he used to whiten the hearth. While he was 
away we blacked it. I can see him now - couldn't black that when I had the job could you? Still - there you are. Oh yes, he always done the - fireplace, Harry did. Or the blackleading, I don't know about every morning, I wouldn't answer for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I suppose you had to look after your younger sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Oh yes, we all had to. And if there was a baby of course - used to have to be taken to the nursery and picked up 'cos - mother wouldn't be home 'til eight or nine o'clock. Nursery closed about five or s
ix. Come out of school, go and get the baby. see, you always had something to do - we were just key kids - yes, we were just key kids just the same but we had our bit to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You had it to do to very large too, your mother not being home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well, yes. Well, there you are, you took it in your stride didn't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Would Harry and Emma do any jobs to help you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes, we - yes, we - me and Harry got on very well together. Of course Emma was so spoilt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well we just went when we were told.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What time would this be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well - eight or nine o'clock. Not too late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no. No. As soon as we could we done all that ourselves. Supervised doing our hairs and that but - not to - wait on us too much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you share the bedroom or bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes. Yes, yes. Of course we would, yes, of course we did. And then as I say as soon as you were
 fourteen, me, I was the oldest, I had to get out and get to service didn't I. 'Course you can imagine why, you didn't realize at the time. But you can - realize now why it wasn't convenient I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Because you'd only have two bedrooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes, two bedrooms. Yes. Mother - when the new babies was born more often than not the bed was taken downstairs. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What were the sleeping arrangements for the household then, there would be the children in one room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 And another room for your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. More often than not a baby in with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You wouldn't have a bathroom then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh - tap out in the yard. We were lucky when we got out own yard and tap and toilet and all that, because you don't get that - di
dn't get that in buildings then. But we did have in our own houses of course. But not when we were upstairs, we had to share. Yes. I remember giving a boy a black - black eye once 'cos - he got out there and he wouldn't come in, and when he did come in he
 got it. Oh and didn't his elder brothers tease him, fancy letting a girl give you a black eye. We had to you know, we used to hold our own. Well we had to, it's just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How often did you bath then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh at least once a week. At least we had the bath in front of the fire. Oh yes, at least once a week. Oh yes, that was a - a ritual.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 When did you put clean clothes on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 As I say at least once a week, more often than not, yes. Oh yes, they was - that was one thing abouts it, we were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Where did the family have their meals?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well all in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Was there any occasion when you ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What sort of cooking equipment did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well of course we had an open - stove - well open - closed range, a big range, and - iron saucepans. Ordinary baking tins.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You didn't have a gas stove at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Not at that time, no, we - when we did have one I think it was out in the yard in - Snowsfield, the first gas stove we had. Used to have a shed out there with the gas stove out there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What time was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh - don't ask me, seven or eight o'clock, somewhere round there, we got to school at nine I know that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What members of the family were present for breakfast, would your father be there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
No. No, he'd always be at work. Of course that was my mother's trouble too - there was no gas or electric. And - six - weeks before Christmas, six weeks after, he was on short time. The first three weeks and the last three wee
ks - there was only one hour, morning and night, and the six weeks direct was two hours morning and night, 'cos there was no electric light, no gas, no nothing. Only had oil lamps. Was always a bad time, Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Would your mother be there when she was working, would she have breakfast with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Oh yes, yes, she wasn't so timed in to get in in the mornings. 'Cos hers was all piecework. She'd get in - I suppose eight or nine o'clock, but she'd see to us. Oh yes, she'd have a little of - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What did you usually have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Oh don't ask me, bread and jam. Porridge. Whatever we could get, whatever was going. If there was eggs we'd get them and if not we wouldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Would it be customary to have eggs and bacon or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no, no, once a week if you were lucky. Sunday mornings, yes. Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How would you go on for your midday meal then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
For a long time we had school dinners. And otherwise mother would leave it and we'd go home and - well, more often than not we had school d
inners, we weren't satisfied we used to go home and cut and carve. There was never any - pull up you know over what we helped ourselves to so long as we - told her what we done. She wouldn't let us do anything without her knowing, she had to know but - th
at was all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Were school dinners a regular thing in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes. Oh yes, that was no disgrace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about the evening meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well we all had the same, that was one thing about my father, whatever he had we had to share. 
One of my uncles in particular - as soon as - and the children, as soon as they left school they had butter and the rest of the family had marg, but my father would never have anything like that. What wasn't good enough for us wasn't good enough for him. 
W
e all had the same. Oh yes, there's that about the old man. No, no. And if - if mother sent out for a herring for him, which she did do, they were only a penny a time them, a penny - hard roed bloater we used to have to go and get, but he'd always share i
t with us. Always - whatever he had he shared. He was ill at one time, this Miss Cotterell that was - sent him half a dozen eggs. And when he went round - she wanted to know if {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}
Warwick{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} had had them. So mother said, no, he shared them with the kids. Oh -they're not ill. They were sent for him. She said, look, he couldn't have ate 'em without }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1996598\charrsid13588098 sharing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
 'em. He couldn't. Oh no. 'Course it wasn't - the best cuts but we always had enough, you know. Joints that we can't cook now, we used to cook in those days. I can't cook flank of beef now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Would you have anything different on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well we mostly had a joint of some sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Your mother often wouldn't get home until eight o'clock in the evening, would you have your meal on your own then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Don't remember much about that really and truly. I suppose we just took it in our stride.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did your mother or father ever bake their own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no, no. No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about making jams or pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No. No convenience for it if you - wanted to.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about medicines, did she have any home recipes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
No, my mother didn't. I don't think she was very keen on it. Granny did but - my mother I don't think was very keen on it. We - we had quite a good doctor, Doctor Burrows, he wasn't bad,
 out of Bermondsey. And of course we lived so near to Guys that the least little thing used to run round there. And you could get round into casualty a lot different to what you can now. You could go without a doctor's letter, you know. I'll tell you some
t
hing about Guys you won't - you won't hardly believe. But I remember Guys when we went in the main gate where the statue is now along the colonnade, on the left had side used to be the casualty and they used to do all the fingers and breaks and that all u
nder a big arc lamp in the middle. Then they gradually got the - cubicles round there. And of course it was after that that they built the other - part.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you ever have a garden, were you ever able to grow vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh never - not vegetables. - After always, like me, always had a few }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1996598\charrsid13588098 f}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 lowers around, a little bit of front garden or a few boxes, always had something, but we never grew veg. Not worth it. No, not worth it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you ever have tinned or dried vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no. Never thoug
ht of. Oh no, never thought of. If you got a tin of salmon that was as much and then I doubt if the old man would fancy it. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about livestock, did your father ever keep any hens or rabbits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh we had - we used to perhaps have a couple of ducks at Christmastime you know, in the winter, or a chicken, but not much. He had -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 This was to fatten them up for meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes, that's right. He - he went into bantam cooks at one time, and - they were lovely too, they were only little cheeky l
ittle beggars. And the neighbours }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1996598\charrsid13588098 complain}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
 This is the joke. The neighbours complained so - the sanitary people came down, they said, well they were quite all right, but - neighbours complaining, he's got to get rid of them. So he said, have I got to get o
f rid of them, he said, I'll give 'em a roasting before I do. He got up about every hour all night long and went out there with a candle and set 'em off crowing. He done that - he done that all the days that he had before he got rid of them. Oh if you get
 over our lot you get over something. Oh he did lead 'em a life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How many times a week do you think you had meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh practically every day. Yes. Oh yes. 'Cos it was cheap. And - just across - the road there they were a packing place, we could get
 the - cracked eggs. Get bowls and bowls of those. Uncle Joe come up one time, I can see him now, 'cos he was never out of work, he had a good job down in the Arsenal, he was a fitter, and he came up this day and my father was out of work, mother's frying
 
this big panful of eggs. And he said - he said, well Charlie you're out of work but you're living better than we are. But they didn't live not the same as we did, they lived a different way but my father always said they were - mean you know. 'Cos he was 
heavy with it. When it was there we had it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about tinned meat, did you ever have tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Very seldom - no, I don't think we had it at all, don't think - don't remember even seeing it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about rabbit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes, you got rabbits, they used to be and two and three and - next door to nothing weren't they. Yes, we used to have rabbits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You never used to get any from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no, no, you couldn't get anything like that round Bermondsey, no. Go round the skin market and
 get the bullocks cheek and all that cheap. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 So really your shopping was a matter of finding the best bargain?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. And - a lot of your money sort of thing. Do a lot of extra cooking, but it got cooked, and the good was there, I
 mean you - when it got cold you could cut it, there was something in it. There isn't anything in this what we get now, nothing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Do you remember seeing your mother having less food so the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well that I couldn't tell 
you because, as I say, she went to work, and - no, I don't think she went without exactly, I don't say there was a lot at times. But I can't - can't imagine her - she may have done, as I say, I wouldn't know would I. 'Cos she was cute like that, she would
n't let us know. No, she wouldn't let us know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Were you allowed to talk during meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I think so. I don't think they ever smothered us, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What would your parents attitude be if you left some food uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I don't know that we did, but I don't think it - well if you didn't want it you didn't want it, but -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 They wouldn't make you eat it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, I don't think so. No, I can see - I can remember plates being cleared and all chucked the back of the fir
e, it wasn't put - anywhere to go bad, it was all burnt, all that sort of thing. Potato peelings and all that was all - burnt up - the back of the fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 If there was something on the table you wanted, such as the salt, could you just help yourself or did you have to ask for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no, we reached over and got it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 If it was there, yes. Oh yes, if it was there, yes. 'Course if it wasn't there you knew you couldn't ask but - oh we did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Could you bring toys or books to the table at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I don't think we did, I think father would put the bar up at that. I don't know much but I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 My brother was left
 handed, but they knocked that out of him at school. Or else - the old man could use both hands, so I don't think we were - taught you know, any different, we could go our own way with regard to that. But father could use both hands, and when he was worki
n
g on the roads - swinging a sledge, he used to get a shilling a day more than the rest in the gang, 'cos when that hand got tired he could put it in that. I do remember that much. And Harry was left handed and - they knocked it out of him at school. They 
wouldn't let you be left handed then. That boy's left handed, that - grandson.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh I think when we were ready, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You didn't have to wait for everyone else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, I - I expect it was all - we were all finished together I should think, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you say grace at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you always have the same places at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well I know father had his corner, but what we done I - I - I suppose we did really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did all the family sit at the table together for the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes, if were in we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Who served the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh mother would dish it up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How would she dish it up, from saucepans onto the plates?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I should think so, yes, I should think so, it wasn't 'til later years we got the - dinner service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Where did your younger brother and sister sit before they could feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 We had a high chair. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Who fed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well I suppose mother did, perhaps we did, perhaps we took it in turns, I wouldn't know. Nobody went without if there was anything there.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Do you know how old they'd be when they were allowed up to the table out of the high }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1996598\charrsid13588098 chair}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 ? Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Oh yes, I used to say to the girls at school, oh all right, wait a minute, I'll got home and ask my mother. She'd tell me. Oh yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 So you had a good relationship with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Was she an affectionate sort of person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well, no, no, no, we - we none of us are, we don't kiss and cuddle and all that, no. No, we didn't do anything of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 But if you had any worries you could share them with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Oh yes, you could go in and ask her anything, she'd tell you
. If she knew herself, if - if she didn't think she would she - shove us if, but - we'd have a go.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
In those days people say they found it very difficult to ask their mother things, especially girls, often they grew up in ignorance of all sexual matters particularly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 They felt their mother never warned them what to expect and a lot of them never knew anything about childbirth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well they tell you that but mind you it's all giver because they used to tell one another at school.
 And as I say, I used to say, all right, I'll ask my mother, she'll tell me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 But you were on good terms with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes. And of course my mother worked in a factory and they didn't eat it. Believe you me, they didn't eat it. One wo
man'd go in and she'd say, my old man's outside - out with so and so. What do you care, he's got enough left for you. See what I mean, there was that about it, it was - very rough. Yes, very rough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did your father show affection or was he the same as your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Oh he was all right, oh yes. Yes, he was all right. Yes. Oh yes. Yes. He wasn't bad at all. I don't know about asking him anything - out the way because - well, you just wouldn't. And you'd be told to put your frock down and sit differen
t to that, and don't - but - it'd be half a dozen words and done with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh, yes please and no thank you and - can we and can't we, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did your parents bring know you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in certain ways or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well I think they preferred us to, but we didn't always. And we were drove to church I'll tell you that for nothing. Drove to church Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What would your parents say if you came in and said another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Serve you right, go back and hit 'em back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 So they'd teach you to stick up for yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Oh yes. Don't come crying to me, go back and hit 'em back, that's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you'd grow up to be?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh I think much as we are. Much as we are I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did they consider certain things as important in life? You say your mother was very straightforward with everyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 She thought honesty was quite important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Oh that was rubbed into us. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Was there any other things like this they particularly emphasized?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, I think - had we been out that way the old man would have encouraged us to go to evening classes
 and that but - there you are, we didn't and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh they could have ago when they had a row, but - we weren't allowed to. Oh no. Oh no, we weren't allowed to. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 If grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 They didn't like it if we did. We might get a back hander. Yes. Specially if we put a spoke in that they didn't want us to. Oh yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 If you did anything that your parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Can't remember much, I 
know we didn't do it very often. They didn't knock us about, not - all that much, we might get a backhander if we wanted it, but - I don't think - I think we got thoroughly told off and that was that. And of course there was more discipline at school. See
 
and they - perhaps they'd threaten us with running us up there or doing this or doing that but - and of course the police had more - they used to walk about with white gloves you know, and if we looked sideways you'd get wallop off of them. Oh yes. They d
a
ren't do it now. Often I think when these kids are going wild out here if a policeman could just lay hold of them and shake them - not knock them about, just shake them, it would make that difference. But when you get little kids like that say, oh well, t
hey mustn't hit me - see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Was discipline handled by one parent or both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no, both. Both - mother mostly. Yes, mother mostly, we were - I think we were a bit scared of the old man, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Do you remember any particular occasion when you were punished? Anything stick out in your mind?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well there's only one that sticks out in my mind, I don't know exactly what my brother done, but he went to bash him, he was in a right paddy. And he ran upstairs, the boy did. My mother got the fo
ot of the stairs and she said, well if Charlie passes me you jump the window. But it didn't get that far. But - that's what I can't understand, women letting a baby be knocked about, because my mother wouldn't, she'd take it herself, she wouldn't let us h
ave it. Not off of him. That was the only time that I know of, you know, that it was really rough. I don't know what he'd done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 But it upset your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh he was really mad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Do you remember how you felt about being punished at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, I think we took it. I think if we deserved it we got it and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Would you say that you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents or was one more important than the other?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh both. And of course they b
oth had church education so that they were both - you know, we were driven to church. Not that we didn't mind going 'cos it was the only treats we got, you know that don't you. Used to get the outings and all from church. but - otherwise I don't - I think
 one backed the other as far as that went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 When you were a child what would happen on your birthday, would this be different from any other day or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no, you just took it in your stride. If there was any money around you'd get a extra bit of
 cake at teatime or whatnot but not an awful lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you receive any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Might have got a bit, but not a lot. We didn't look for a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about guests, would you have a party or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Might have a few kids in but then you weren't allowed to pull the place to pieces. There wasn't room enough really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 But it would be marked in some way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes, oh yes, we all had our birthdays, always - had a birthday cake as far as I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about Christmas Day, what would you do with your mother and father then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Christmas - we done all right Christmas. Oh yes, we done all right Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you have a tree in those days, was that customary or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 It was, but I don't think we did. I don't think we bother
ed with trees, we had - Christmas - stockings, we hung them up, I don't say we had a lot in them. But we did have stockings. A few coppers, a bit of fruit. A toy according to what was going. As I say, nobody had a lot, there was no cutting families out, n
ot this kid next door's got a bike and you've got to have a motor bike or any of that, there was none of that then. That came along more in the first war. When the women handled the money. Talking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about musical instruments, did you have any in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
No, we didn't have any. No. The old man would not go into debt. If you wanted a piano you just couldn't afford it and you just didn't get it and that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 He only had what he could pay for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes. And we never had what h
e called a room to look at. Every room in the house was in use. He wouldn't have a room to look at, not him. He was the guv'nor that far.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you ever make music together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes, he could sit down in the in the chair and keep everybody singing and dancing with the old fashioned choruses and that, oh yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Would he do this while you were children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes. Mother could too. Certain amount. But father could. Feet would -be going and ours all going with it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Were there any games you played together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well darts. Not darts, draughts you call 'em, I call 'em checkers. - But - not a lot I don't think. We used to sit and read. I suppose - ludo is it or something of that sort but not an awful lot. W
e had clubs and that you know we used to go out to at night. Harry was in the Scouts. One holiday Monday there was a terrific row. The kids had pulled a mattress to pieces out in the street and evidently they'd been using the cover for a tent. My mother h
appened to go out and this woman said, that so and so Harry Warwick. My mother said, oh no it ain't. Oh yes it is, She said, it ai}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1996598\charrsid13588098 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 't. He's right down the line, he's gone out with his father. The woman said, you tell me what I saw woman. 'Cos my mother was 
always at work. So she said, I am. They had an up and a downer but it all sorted itself out, poor Harry copped out, but - it wasn't him at all, he was right up the line. Out with his father 'Cos they used to out what they had to say then, I mean, they'd g
o for one another and then it was all over.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 This was more common in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Oh yes. Yes. There was no sulk or anything. No, they'd just spit fire, that was it. I still do. Yes, I still do. You know where you are with those people. But when you get a person that won't answer you you're lost.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What sort of books did you have to read as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well we got library books and I think there was some around of father's that we used to get you know, the likes of Dickens and that. And of co
urse - we lived - right there by the Borough. The old Bermondsey he was very interested in and we used to get it rammed into us, in fact sometimes we'd say, oh he's off again and let it go in one side and out the other. But - he was very keen on the histo
ry of - round about the Borough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 We always had Lloyds. Always had Lloyds Sunday paper. But I don't think we had many during the week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Only the boys books. I used to read them as much as he did. Of more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Were your mother and father keen on reading or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes. They used to have a library book and that. Mother did especially. Father used to get wild, but still, he had to put up with it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did they ever read aloud to you when you were children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Not that I know of, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Can you remember a funeral in the family before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Could you tell us anything about what happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well as far as we went we had the funeral and we just - went down, buried the baby, and came back. But the worst ever - well, the worst -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 This would be one of your sisters?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes, one of the babies, I don't know whether it'd be a brother or sister. But - my aunt 1}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\super\insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 st}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098  a boy twelve years old, yes, he was twelve. The grandmother had been a black woman. The grandfather was a regular soldier in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}India{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 and - married this woman, had the two children, Uncle Tom and sister, we never saw the sister. But Uncle Tom got back here. He was all right until he was - I don't know wh
ether it was seventy, he was getting well on anyway before he died, but she had an awful lot of trouble with her children. And doctors didn't seem to understand them. It was as though they went into T.B. and yet they said it wasn't. Well this boy, twelve 
-
 don't know whether it was ten or twelve, he was a boy at school anyway, the school kids all lined up while we were going out to the funeral. And - they asked the - undertaker to do it as cheap as he could - at that time, which the man did. Took him right
 from Bermondsey to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Paisley{\*\xmlclose}, which needn't have happened. My grandfather was buried in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Paisley{\*\xmlclose}
 so of course - Aunt Florrie took the boy there. All the way home - I don't think Uncle Tom passed a pub. He kept pulling up. He was well oiled time he got - and m
y father didn't go, he very seldom did go to a funeral, but my mother was very annoyed. She - 'course she turned round, she said, they've asked - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Albion{\*\xmlclose}
 was the undertaker's name - to do it as cheap as he can and this was what they're doing. My mother was raving.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes, I went with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How old were you at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
I must have been getting on for twenty. Yes, I must have been getting of for twenty, 'cos this was my mother's youngest sister, there's only seventeen years between me and her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You said something about them lining up the schoolchildren?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Yes. The schoolchildren. Well, of course - he was a schoolboy and he was pretty popular too, young - Georgie his name was. Yes, and they - got in the street as he was ca
rried out. 'Cos - you see, the crowds do that now don't you. Seems as though it's a - hang over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Who attended, was it all the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes, Aunt Florrie, Uncle Tom. I don't know if any of the youngsters went. Couldn't have been, 'cos she had an awful big family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you wear morunging clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Oh yes, that had to be. Even for a baby you were - black from top to bottom. Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 It must have been quite an expense?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 It was really. Although of course you got the - mate
rial cheap. And there was generally a neighbour that would run it up. I've heard my mother say with her - neighbours and that, one in particular, sat up all night and made all the frills by hands, 'Cos Roman Catholics don't leave their - bed you know, the
y stay with then.; And - this woman had stayed and made all the clothes by hand. But - I can't imagine any of us doing it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Were you taken out visiting neighbours or friends and relatives very much by your parents while you were a child at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Not visiting, no. No, not an awful lot. My father always used to sort of watch points, he never went - what he couldn't afford, it just didn't come off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Were you taken out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes, he used to take us out Bank Holidays. Always Bank Holidays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Where would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Either Greenwich Park. 'Cos we could go on - a tram and come back by boat or go by boat and come back by tram on the return ticket. It was only tuppence or threepence return. I think it was threepence to Battersea and tuppence to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Greenwich{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. My mother used to say, all right, you're going to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Greenwich
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} are you? I'm not going to your brother Joe's. No, Bess, we won't go there. He'd get us to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Greenwich{\*\xmlclose}, then we'd get across {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Greenwich{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Park{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} right across Blackheath, across Shooters Hill,
 we'd finish up at Plumstead. Us kids loved it, we used to get half a - half sovereign - golden half sovereign - Uncle Joe or - Cousin Neil used to give us. We were pleased as punch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 That must have been a fortune in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 It was. One time Lil said to my brother, Here you are Harry boy, here's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1996598\charrsid13588098  }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 a ha'penny. He took it, barely said thank you. When we got along the street mother said, what did Lil give you? It was half a sovereign. He could have gone back and said thanks you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How often would you end up seeing this uncle, many times a year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Two or three times. Yes. And after he retired and that father used to have the tuppence all the way to Plumstead and go and see them, and they had their own house there. Very nice house. 'Cos he'd worked steady, my father was never steady.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What sort of job did he have, do you remember?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 My father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You uncle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 He was supposed to be official in the Arsenal. He worked in the Arsenal all his life. And he got father there during the Bo
er War. Worked there during the Boer War. And when you work at the Arsenal you had to work a fortnight before you get any money, you see. And it appears that - father had to borrow his fare to go backwards and forwards from 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}London{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Bridge{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and etcetera etcet
era and he didn't see Uncle Joe all the time that first fortnight. The second fortnight he met him. He always had a grievance and every time he had a row with Uncle Joe he used to bring that up, I didn't see you for the fortnight, but as soon as I got me 
m
oney I had it. Then when the second war broke out as I say I went on munitions, I was on gas masks. And we wasn't supposed to go from one lot of munitions to the other, but I wanted to go down the; Arsenal, me father said I wasn't to go. Three miles to wa
l
k from the gate to danger buildings. 'Cos I wanted the money didn't I. And - eventually I got there. But I had to give a previous reference - to get that job, but I got it. And - then as I say, my sister couldn't get a job, she's seven years younger, and 
s
he was under eighteen, mother was over forty, her work come under luxuries, so neither of them could get any work - work worth having. And when I turned in this first job I said, well look, it's the same name, same address, we're paid every night, go and 
c
hance your luck. So she went in, she got the job. She done it for months. Suddenly she had to put her own name and address - on a bit of paper. She said, what will I do. I said, sign your own name, don't sign mine, put Emma. And she put Emma and it was on
ly to check on her handwriting. And she got a better job. She was checker. She was - made, she was all right. And - they asked mother could she cook potatoes. She said, I've cooked 'em all my life, and she went on Smith's crisps. How that came about.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Before 1918 did you ever go away on a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
I think I went about - to - Southend about once, but Leigh-on-Sea about once, it was only half a crown return fare, I don't know what we paid -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Would this be for the day, not for a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes, I think it was for a week, I think it was from the Girls Friendly Society from church. Went with a party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Was this before you left school or after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 After. After. Yes. While we were at school we went with the Country Holiday Fund.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What was that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
That was from day school, we used to go in the country, not too far down. You know - were boarded out with different families. Last time I went my Emma was getting - Emma wasn't old enough and it was the last time I could go. So they stretched a
 point for her to come with me. Nice little spoilt brat she was. And we had a spoilt brat in the house. We had to go down to a stream to get the water. Not stir the mud up, just - take the water off the top of the stream which we done. Coming back this ki
d shuts the gate so that we couldn't get through. My Emma chucks it over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Whereabouts in the countryside was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I think it was Warwickshire somewhere, it was - right in the country, we were boarded out with people that were - farm labourers so
rt of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How did this holiday thing work, was it free?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Oh no, no, you paid so much a week. And my mother used to pay everything, and she got such a good name that - if there was anything going - I think it was only tuppence or threepence, pe
rhaps sixpence a week, but when she took on to do anything she done it. And - I think Harry and Emma went several years, I don't remember going only the once myself. And I know I had my Emma with me. Haven't forgiven her either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about weekends, how would you spend your Saturday in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well there was always a bit of - always a bit of cleaning to do, mother used to be at work 'til two o'clock. More often than not we used to take the baby to meet her, take the washing up to meet her at w
ork and go into the Leamington Street baths. Southwark there. And that was the afternoon. Perhaps in the meantime run home again and make a jug of tea and take back to her. Oh we used to get the day in all right. Yes, it wasn't too bad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Sundays of course church, wash up, Sunday school. Morning and afternoon, evening. Anywhere where there was treats going we were there. It was only a barney.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you have different clothes for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes, always. That's one grievan
ce I've got about me mother, I told her about 'til the day she died. We always had Sunday boots and Sunday clothes, and I'd got new button up high legged boots - is that still running - and - one button came off, the lot came off. Of course they stayed of
f
 didn't they 'til Sunday morning. I go to sew them on. She said, you don't, it's Sunday. I go to get me school boots, they're lace ups. She says, you don't, it's Sunday, you've got Sunday boots. So she made me go to church like that. I told her of it 'til
 the day she died.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 So your parents thought it wrong to work on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
She did at that time, she got over it but - that - that was one thing with my mother, principles for us but not for her if she didn't think fit. 'Course you don't realize it at the time. No, there's a lot that you don't realize at the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Would she never let you work while you were children though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes, oh if there was anything to do we had to do it Sunday, it was just the sewing - that I'd had all the week t
o do it you see, and I hadn't done it all the week so that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 So it was more to teach you a lesson than anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I expect so. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Were you allowed to play games on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did your parents go to a place of worship or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Very often Sunday nights, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Your father as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What denomination was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Church of England. Actually father was stricter than mother in that line, 'cos - mother's - mother's father was a Unitarian, t
hat's Greek to me but - I believe he was a good man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 About how often would your parents go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Nearly every Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you attend the adult service while you were still a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, we used to go somewhere else where we could have a sing-song.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Where did you attend as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well we went to Church of England in the Sunday morning, that was got to. But after that there was a Methodist just across in Long Lane. We used to go there they used to put on lantern slides and - sing-s
ong and all that. Sunday afternoon, where did we get to. Probably at the church, only in Sunday school in another part.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 This way you'd get two outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You're telling me. Go into row one }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1996598\charrsid13588098 Ascension}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098  day, all dressed up to go out, we had to go to church }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1996598\charrsid13588098 Ascension}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
 day, and then they took us out in the afternoon. Of course going to church all dressed up, teachers meet us. You dressed up for school? No ma'am. We always had to say ma'am to our teachers. No, we're going to church. Oh that was wrong, but
 still, we done it. Can't you imagine it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well - only as far as Ruskin Park or anywhere like that, of course with coach and four, you know, the open coach - brakes and horses and that, we thought it was marvelous. We got as far as Riddlesdown we were miles away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You were limited to what the horses could do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did they never have a rail outing to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1996598\charrsid13588098 sea code}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Very seldom. Very seldom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Were there any other social activities organized by the church or Sunday schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well we had - as I say, there was one or two clubs - in the evenings we used to go to. And - first aid class, I've done a bit of that, didn't do much good at it but still - pass the time away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did they have a temperance club or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Band of Hope as we used to call it, oh yes. Yes, we all done that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you ever belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No. No. Harry was well away on the altar and all that, he done very well and he was - patr
ol leader in the Scouts until one year they changed their camps. They went sea Scouts and Sea Scouts had their camps and he saw too much of what the priests were up to and - finished. I don't think he went to church hardly after. 'Cos we're like that, we 
t
ake - you know, you're either all right or else you're all wrong with us lot, and - evidently this - Father - forget his name, he caught him, they'd got the bottles of Bass, I know it was Bass, and he said, don't never take on with this Harry. And Harry w
as done with him. That was it. 'Course he was getting fourteen or fifteen by then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No. We knew we should but I don't think we were ever made to. If they didn't make us do anything we didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about grace at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no. No, we never bothered. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes, he was rank Labour. Oh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Was this before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes. When we had the Progressives, the red - when we had the
 three - three corner faiths, that's when the Liberals got - thrown out. 'Cos previous to that he was always Liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Why do you think he held these views, did he ever talk about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well of course - we had - when he was out of work, when you 
had the Tories in or the - whatever you called them then - they were so hard on the young - on the working men, I mean the money was all in a few peoples pockets wasn't it, and they just kept that lot down. And one time he was out of work and he had to ha
ve relief, he lost his vote. And of course that stuck. You see, things like that stick, they don't - and it's there that you can't - forget it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about your mother, what were her views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh she held in with him didn't she.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Can you remember your mother or father voting in a general election before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, no, not to - what, to get into any arguments or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 To go and cast their votes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh I expect they did, I don't remember exactly, I expect they did, 'cos father wouldn't miss anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 In some places at that time men felt they risked losing their job or their house if they voted differently from their employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well of course the - the old man was a right rebel, he wouldn't care, he'd rath
er be out of work than go against his own principles. And he wouldn't work under wages.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Do you know if he ever was under any of this sort of pressure at all or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I think he must have been at times. I think he must have been. 'Cos - we change
d churches at one time because - a priest there - were on the committees for the Bermondsey Vestrv, and he wanted to get right in, he was casual and he wanted to get right in. You see a lot of the priests and clergy had all that authority, they were on al
l
 these committees. That you more or less had to - and one time they were both working, both doing all right. And my mother was sent for to go up to the school for a committee. She cross questioned us, what we'd all been up to. As she went in this room pre
p
ared to say yes please, no thank you, or whatever - you know - quiet. This - from the church turned round, oh she said, Mrs Warwick, you want boots. S - of course mother said, yes please. She thought, well if they're coming we may as well have them. Well,
 
she said, you've got two of them at school, 'cos I had left by then. We'll give you one pair and pay for the other. Well that was that. That was sixpence a week for the other pair and mother paid and she was in the good books again. But she didn't know ho
w
 it was worked out or who done it. Another time - it's coming back to me now, she'd lost a baby - suddenly - died in her arms as a matter of fact - and they were quite happy about it. She'd had Guys doctors, we were in a Guys house, and they were quite ha
p
py about it. But she always blamed one of these lady visitors. My mother was a jumped up too when she thought fit. This woman had taken her round a shawl. So mother said, I don't want the shawl. She said, I've got shawls enough for my baby. My children do
n
't go to your church. I don't want your shawl. That was that. See. When the baby died - somebody, we never knew who - insisted on an inquest. This chap gets up with the - society's - and the doctor told him to sit down. You sit down and mind your own busi
ness. This is all right, always has been all right. So - and my mother always blamed that woman, whether it was her. But it sounds like it. The sort of thing they used to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 They used to try to interfere quite a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You say your father changed his church, what was he trying to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
He wanted to get permanently on the Bermondsey Vestry. To get in with the clergy, that he was known. Well only in recent years, with my brother a few years ago, I was talking like I mi
ght be to you know, he said, you know Carry, he said, if you never get into trouble - the directors never know you. He said, but if you've done something wrong, he said, and then you want a hospital letter, 'cos they used to get letters for Barts, he work
e
d for the Daily Mail, and you want a hospital letter, when your name goes up, oh we don't know him, he's never been in trouble you see, he's gone - but the man that's been on the carpet, oh yes, that's all right. We know what - he comes from so and so. Ju
st one of those things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Were these Guys houses anything like the Peabody Trust or anything like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no, no, they were little houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 And you paid a proper rent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 A regular weekly rent. Oh yes, rent and rates all in together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 They were a full rent were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Weren't - not as far as I know they weren't. 'Cos the rents were very light in those days. No, it wasn't a subsidised, no, the only thing they were good to us - as I say, if we went there we mostly got our - medicines
 and that cheap or - we only paid threepence anytime, perhaps we'd get ours for nothing, and - if any of us were ill and they want - and wanted a bed, the round The Counting House they would get it for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 So they were a bit favourable towards their own tenants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes. Oh yes. Especially to my mother. My mother knew how to talk to people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 So there was a bit of an advantage from a health point of view?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes. Oh yes. Yes. Yes, they were very kind to my mother. Didn't like th
e old man. Collector couldn't stand him, I suppose he used to tick him off, he would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did your parents take part in any political activity other than at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, we weren't - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 They didn't belong to a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, not that I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 When your parents weren't working how would they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well of course mother mostly always was at work. She mostly when to work, I think she preferred work. Then the old man would much about indoors. But he wa
sn't in such a lot, he'd go and - go around and get something, we never went without. Never went without, and of course - you could get cheap food over Leadenhall market and - all round there and we weren't too far away, it was only just over London Bridg
e. We never went without, in fact sometimes I think we used to do better. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did your mother have any interests outside the home, did she belong to any clubs or Women's Institutes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No. Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did she ever go out at all do enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well she'd go out with her mates at work and that at odd times. Have a drink on the way home and all that kind of thing, especially Christmastime. And they always used to get a day off - if there was a funeral. If one of them died, the guv'no
r used to give them a day off, well they behaved themselves while they done their business and after that, well - you'd be lucky when you saw them. Still you knew where they were, you knew the gang they were with you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Would the woman ever go out to a music hall together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes. Oh yes, we used to go out Saturday nights to music hall. 'Course there was the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London
{\*\xmlclose} - in the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}London Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, and - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Surrey{\*\xmlclose}, Gatties in the 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Westminster Bridge Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, the Old - Rotherhithe Hippodrome.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You used to go to these with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Oh yes. Yes, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You used to go to these before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 When did your father get home from work in the evening, what time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well - varied with the daylight really. Yes, mostly always - you know, fairly early in the evenings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How many evenings a week would he spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Mostly every evening until the weekend. Money wouldn't run to it would it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did he attend any clubs or pubs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Not - he 
went to the pubs of course but as far as clubs I don't think so. Of course I don't remember it all. I wasn't very old before he ran out of the - order of Foresters, he was a freemason and then he was ill and I think he ran it out or - I don't know, it dro
pped anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did your father take part in any sport at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, not a lot. No, he wasn't a sport and he didn't - he wasn't called up, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1996598\charrsid13588098 not in}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098  the '14-'18 war, he was too old. Done that all wrong, I don't know if you've heard this bit. He signed on
 for National Service. He was sharpening the tools in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Daltons{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 factory, they smashed the pottery to make shell cakes, and he was working on a fire getting the tools ready for the girls to do the work, I earnt more than he did. See, he signed on, he couldn't
 help himself. Done that all wrong. As the war broke out everybody got patriotic, he signs on for National Service and 'course he cooked his own goose.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Were they on a fixed wage or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Father was. But I think the girls were on a bonus. '
Cos we were down the Arsenal. We never knew what we were going to get. The shops that were on a certain job, we were on cordite - think there was three or four shops on cordite, we all got the same wages and every so often we got a bonus.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did everyone who signed on for National Service get a fixed wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well my father was on a fixed rate. Yes, he was on a fixed rate, and I don't think it was all that good. I've only heard the moan about that, that I earned more than he did. Or I gave up more than he did, I don't know, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Would he have a bet on the horses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, no, he was never a gambler. And that's one thing I thank God my boys are not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs, any boot clubs, sick clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
He - he was saving in the penny bank at one time. Mother lost a baby and he wouldn't draw the money out. And it went bang so she said, serves you right. So that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 He lost all his money did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well - I think he - they got a per
centage, I don't know. I know mother said, serve you right. 'Cos he wouldn't pay insurances. No, he never - chanced anything. He was no gambler at all, no sport whatever. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 As a child who did you play with, your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh - kids
 out in the street. Oh yes, oh we had - and we used to enjoy ourselves, we had hoops and hopscotch and all sorts of things, you never see the kids play quiet now. Holiday Mondays if we didn't go out for the day mother and father or father - the men, used 
to have the brewers ropes and turn 'em for skipping and all }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1996598\charrsid13588098 that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 , but you never see it nowadays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 For all the kids in the street?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes. Go and have a drink on the dinner time and on the afternoons after that they'd - come out with you. When o
ne - you know, there wasn't much traffic in those little turnings. One - one on the pavement that way and us kids - in the middle sort of thing. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You'd have several of the parents and all the neighbourhood children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes. All neighbours. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How did you get on with hour brothers and sisters, was there anyone you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Oh - my brother, I still am. I still am with him. 'Course Emma was all right but as I say, she only had to turn the tap on and we got a backhander so - we had to tolerate her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Where did you play as a rule?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No where else to play, only in the street was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you ever go to any of the parks as children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes, we had {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Guys{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Park{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} just off of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Kipling Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} there, we used t
o go in there quite a lot. And that - used to go up a slope to that. One of our friends - rushed down the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1996598\charrsid13588098 slope}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
 and under a horse and cart, lost her arm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Would you ever go and play in other childrens homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Not a lot. Not a lot. There wasn't roo
m really. And of course you opened the street door and went straight up the stairs, we used to get on the stairs in one another's places. Get up there say with dolls clothes and all that sort of thing but - plait one another's hair. 'Cos we all had long h
air in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What other sort of games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh I - I think I've told you nearly all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Skipping and hopscotch and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes, I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh rather, we did didn't we. There was always plenty of water in the tap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Were you free to play with anyone you wanted to or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I think so, I don't think there was any bar put up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Your mother didn't discourage you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no. Oh no, no. Well we sorted out ourselves didn't we.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 In what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well in people - if they weren't just as clean as we liked and we'd got nice long hair and that - we didn't think they were suitable, well they - we just cold - shouldered 'em, we done all that ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 It was just a matter of you doing it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Oh no, we weren't allowed to go in and tell tales.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 While you were still at school did you belong to any youth organizations, not connected with the churc
h, you say your brother belonged to the Scouts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No. No. There wasn't much for girls. Girls Friendly Society, but of course that was church again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What did you used to do with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well - just - puzzles and games and - nothing much out the way, little bit of - nagging, you know, the usual.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 They would have a hall would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes, yes, there's plenty of halls because - all belongs to Charterhouse Mission. They've got nearly all that street now I believe.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you have any hobbies then, did you collect anything or keep any pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Father used to have - we always had birds, therefore none of us liked cats. He always had birds, the old man did, but otherwise there wasn't much in that line. I think we had a rabbit now and again but not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you go out walking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, just played around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Or cycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Just stayed in your local area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Not a lot. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You used to go to the music hall while you were still at school, how about theatres or cinemas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Couldn't do - no, there weren't any cinemas were there, or not much. They were just coming, and - I don't think we went at all. But - they used to do the serials. And I remember one of the o
ld neighbours always used to keep one of the grandchildren at home to take her to the pictures to read the - 'cos she couldn't read or write. But we never went as far as I remember. I don't think we liked it. I think mother and father said they weren't go
ing to sit in the dark and that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did your parents give you any pocket money while you were a schoolgirl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes, yes, only a couple of coppers but we did get it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Was this regular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes. Regular if - when they were at work, of course we knew that if they weren't we couldn't have it, that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What did you spend your money on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Sweets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after her house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Only neighbours, no, nobody. Granny 
used to do our sewing for us, she was very very good at it, mother's mother. 'Cos he lost his mother and father when he was - young. That's how my sister got named Emma. She was born during the - Boer War in 1900, he came home from work this morning and h
e said, you can have her Emma or Eliza and she said, oh well, we'll have it Emma. Oh he said, thank God, he said, they've all got Eliza's, I'll be the only one with Emma. Emma was his sister. He'd lost her as a - child or - before. Lost his mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You say neighbours would help, in what ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well - that time my mother was very ill - the woman came in and collected up every bit of washing. Took it out and done it. Every bit you know and done it and brought it back. Whether she was paid afterwards 
or what happened I wouldn't know, but I know she came in and done it and - they used to do things for one another, but now they won't do a thing unless they're paid for it. Makes me sick, along here - said, well Anne was good to you you know when you was 
ill. Oh well, I paid her. Well we wouldn't look for that. In fact I'd be offended.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Do you remember what happened when your younger brothers or sisters were born, how your mother got on then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well we used to have Guys doctors. Mostly Guys doctors
. Must send for them and they'd come and that was that. Then they'd come one or two days afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How did the family get on for cooking and cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh we all mucked in didn't we. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Would neighbours help at times like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I suppose they would if they - thought. I don't - don't remember much about that really. I know we all kept living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you have any relatives living near, you say your father wasn't too keen on his relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, no, his brother of course lived at
 Plumstead, that was the only one. Oh, there was one in the Borough, Uncle Alf lived across in the Borough, we didn't see much of him, the two women didn't get on did they, and - my mother's sister lived down more {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
South Bermondsey{\*\xmlclose}, Aunt Florrie. Granny didn't live too far away. And when he was at work he used to send her a sixpence every Sunday morning. That was a religion. He was very good to granny in his way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Who used to take it to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh we had to take it. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 So you'd see your granny quite often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes. At least once a week. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 If you saw your uncles or if they saw them would they visit them at home or would they see them at the local?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no, no, we'd go into one another's houses. We'd be sent down with a me
ssage, perhaps if there was a barney or a bit of a grievance after a week or two or a day or two - take this down and, you know, sort of smooth things over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 And then your parents would go and visit them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes, that's right. Kids always got sent to do the first move.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did your parents have many friends apart from relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
I think my father was fairly popular. You see - he had been a freemason as I say and you Findlaters, the foot of London Bridge, the big pub round the corner, when he 
was really hard up if he had his entrance fee he'd go in there and get a drink, and of course we all done all right. Always took one or two of us kids with him. And there'd be a couple of bob each and he'd come out with a couple of bob. And of course, tha
t was a big help in those days. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did your mother and father share the same friends or did your mother have different friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well mother had her friends at work. And of course as I say, he had - actually he was just that shade better off tha
n - better educated - looks and everything. Just that big - not enough - not a lot but it was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Were these friends ever invited into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh nobody was left outside. Everybody was asked in. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How often would they have friends round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Not too often. Once a - once a fortnight, a month or so, not too often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Would they be offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 If there was anything there, oh yes, always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Were there particular occasions or would people just call in casually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Oh come in when they thought, you know, if they were around, if they - as I say, if Uncle Joe was up from Plumstead, if he thought he'd come in, we never knew when he was coming in, it's the same with Aunt Florrie, if she called on my moth
er we wouldn't know never - there was no writing then, no sending postcards or anything. No, none of that. No. Too expensive.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Would neighbours call in just casually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Not a lot. Mother didn't encourage a lot of that. She was friendly with them, s
ame as I am here, but not to have them in and out all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 People often tell us that in those days people made their own }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1996598\charrsid13588098 amusements}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 , what do you think your parents did when they got together with their friends, when they were having an evening at home, what sort of entertainments would they have?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well just a sing-song. Not a lot otherwise. We'd have a cup of tea and that indoors and then I think they'd go up the pub for an hour or two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did your parents ever go out to visit neighbours or go round neighbours houses or friends houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Not a lot, no. Not a lot. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 People divide society into different social classes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes. You got it very much - very very much, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Can you tell us about the different groupings before 1918 as you saw it at that time? What were the different social groups before 1918?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well of course you got a lot of people then worse than they are now living on their wits. Then of course you were just that much above them weren't they - wer
en't you, and you kept away from them. And it was the same with schools. I mean the school we went to, we went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Laxton Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 in Long Lane, it's a secondary now, we thought we were a bit better than those that went to - Snowsfield school, you know. Wheth
er it was I don't know, I think it must have been because our governess or headmistress used to take us out a lot. Now, the headmistress was allowed so much money for parties or - you know, to spend how she liked on us. Well she spent it on tram fares - c
arting us about, we never got any parties at our school, we got all - education.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 This seems quite advanced?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well, lots of times - I am advanced, only I was always sick on a tram, and consequently by the time I got to the National Gallery or anywh
ere like that - it was going in one side and out the other, and if I could get the back of the group and take the mickey out of somebody that suited me better than all that lecture. But there are times when people ask me about - artists and that, like Bot
ticelli and Turner and different names that stick, they look at me as much as to say, where the hell have you had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You think this was from your schooling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes, definitely. Certainly wasn't from anywhere else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 So the neighbourhood school seemed better?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
It was a better school, yes, and we were right there. And of course as I say, father and mother, or father particularly would - keep us above that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What social group would you put your own family into at that time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well mor
e or less - good working class. Not artisans, not - not mechanics. 'Cos just above my father are the crowd that all voted - Conservative and have got not time for us if you understand. I mean, I get the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What sort of jobs are you thinking of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 W
ell master - carpenters and builders and all that you see. Like Uncle - yes, like Uncle Joe had. 'Cos Uncle Joe - yes, yes, they were all - sure of their jobs but my father would never be sure of his job. In fact, he said a man that stuck at a job all his
 life wasn't worth knowing. He believed in - mixing, having a change.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You said there was a group who lived by their wits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes, you got a lot of that round -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What would you call them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well they were - certainly below us weren't they. I wouldn't know exactly but they were - we had an awful lot -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Would you class them as rough or scroungers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes, they were - you know, they were really rough criminals really, and they - sort of went right through families like that. This gan
g and the other gang, but it was the family right the way through.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 So there were about three groups within the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What would you say were the other groups then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Schoolteachers and likes of that, well of course they were way up weren't they. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Where would you put a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1996598\charrsid13588098 white-collar}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098  worker at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well they'd be more - educated - just that shade better than my father although he could put a collar on and be as good as any of them. Of course that was experience with him. But - oh they weren't - looked on as - you know, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1996598\charrsid13588098 pen pushers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
 and that sort of thing, they weren't all that made a fuss of because they didn't get the money that the labourers got. That's what counted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about people like postmen or railway workers, how were they classed then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well of course they were classed as mugs because they were working under pay although they were working steady all the time, but it was very very poor pay. Shocking poor pay. But there you
 are, they got into that rut. And - they stayed in it, and that didn't suit the old man. Doesn't suit my youngest boy you know. My eldest one's more steady, but the young one -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Oh no. No, we always had to say yes please, no thank you and be - reasonable. Oh no, we didn't - and it we had our doubts about anybody we wouldn't know, we were always told not to know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You say you had to call your schoolmistresses ma'am, were you taught to call anyone else madam or sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well we always did in those days. I mean - clergy and all that, as my brother was talking to one - where he's living now, his wife goes to one or two meetings, he don't, and they g
o in and see him and he told him he said, of course when we were boys we used to have to doff our caps to the likes of you. That was it wasn't it, you done it - automatically.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Would you doff your caps to other people other than the clergy or the schoolteachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
I don't think so. No. I don't think so. No, 'course as I say we weren't brought up to be inferior to anybody, we were - on a level with all the people we mixed with - except those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in this way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, not out of the way, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 In your district who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You mean like the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1996598\charrsid13588098 councillors}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098  and - and landlord collectors and - likes of that. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Who else would you include? Why were these people considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Don't ask me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What sort of people would you say went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Only those that wanted something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 People who wanted something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes. You may as well have it, that - that's all we went for 
- to keep in with them and that. They were - they'd got the authority, we hadn't. They knew where to put their fingers on what was needed.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 So you used them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. You had to. Go betweens. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh they were all the same, they were all on the committees and all just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 So you don't think there was much difference between them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I don't think so. - No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about shopkeepers in those days, where would you class them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well of course we had a ver
y old fashioned shop, Hobdens, don't know if you've herd of them in Long Lane Bermondsey, and he had one or two shops around. And his nephew used to help in the shop, and I could twist him round me little finger, he always gave me extra make weight and - 
if there was anything wanted. I think one time he'd given me the wrong change and I gave it back to him and after that he couldn't do anything wrong that kind of thing. Yes, we always got treated all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Who did these sort of people mix with, did the shopkeepers go in the local pub and mix with the working class or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well I think if they went - when they were finished work they went home, whether they mixed in as I say I wouldn't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about schoolteachers or the clergy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh th
ey didn't. No, they didn't. They had their own, they - didn't mix with us. No, the Salvation Army were the first lot that done that, the tub thumpers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Where you lived in Bermondsey did all the people in the working class have the same standard of livi
ng or would you say there were different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no, no, we had the same standard, pretty well the same standard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Do you think that one group - you talked about the artisans being a little above you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 They didn't live as good as us. No. 
They might have a proper joint on the Sunday and it had to last all the week. Well we wouldn't, we'd have - a bit every day different.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Why do you think you managed to live better then, if you didn't have the same wages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well it was more - it wa
s there and what was there was finished. It wasn't - put away for the next meal or hashed up for the day after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 It was more an attitude of mind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Do you think that any one of these groups in the working class felt superior to the others at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Not unless it was my father when he started arguing with any of them. 'Cos as I say, he - he did have it in a way. He'd been to church school and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Was there much of a distinction between craftsmen and labourers in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well one depended on the other, I don't know that there was much distinction when they were working. Because I mean you get the blacksmith, and father was what they called a blacksmith's hammerman, but they couldn't work one without the other. So
 they worked together. And if one man got that he understood how the other one worked - they preferred that one - to work together. 'Cos with blacksmiths some of the work was very tricky, father would have a sledgehammer and had to hit the - top of that p
incer, without hitting the other man's fingers, you see. Yes. Yes. He used to say you could take that pencil out of your mouth and I'll hit it and I won't hit your fingers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Do you remember anything about builders labourers as compared with carpenters o
r bricklayers, where they're not quite so close together, do you remember any difference between them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Do you think your mother and father had the same attitude to people in different social groups or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, I don't think so, I think we were all - as good as you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to any particular social group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You don't think she'd be conscious of this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Was it possible in that time before 1918 to move from one social class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Oh yes, people used to take a bigger house and get into a - a - I mean South Bermondsey - was inclined to be a bit better socially than when where we lived at the foot of London Bridge. On the other hand there was no more money there. Ju
st bigger houses, perhaps more lodgers. Where we had a four roomed house to ourselves, perhaps a six roomed house and two or three rooms would be let. So they weren't any better off. Ghey were wider streets, and - you've heard about Salter. He was an M.P.
 for Bermondsey. He had trees planted, 'cos he thought that was absorbing the dust and dirt and - that was more South Bermondsey, they - it was a better outlook up there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Would this be a case of going from the working class to the middle class or just more or less moving to a different district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Just moving district, I don't think there was much in it really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Do you think it was possible to move from the working class to the middle class in those days, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well - I s
uppose there was if the boy won a scholarship or got on a bit, but - it was a bit difficult, it was a bit - there was too much class distinction. My father was very annoyed. This brother of mine was very good at drawing. They went for father to know what 
h
e was going to do. Father said well he thought he'd make a good draughtsman. But - on account of father being in and out of work and one thing and another the headmaster said, oh no, and that was that. Harry had to take - pot luck. See, it was all sort of
 - keep you where you are. Don't matter how good you were you stayed where you were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Do you remember anyone being described as a real lady or a real gentleman in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Only the old man. Yes, I remember Aunt Florrie saying that one time, I d
on't know what was brought up, talking - I was talking like I might be to you and two or three of her children were there, and she said - oh yes, the Warwicks always were. Why I don't know. But the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Warwicks{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} always were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You definitely as a family thought you had this bit of an edge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes, yes, on those - on my mother's family, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You say you remember the policemen coming round and they'd give the children a flick with their gloves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How do you think police treated people on the whole in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well as long as you were all right they were all right, but of course if they were running anybody in or anything they could be spiteful. Oh yes. But - generally speaking they were just ordinary. We always found them all ri
ght. And was never afraid of them. Oh no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You're mother didn't say she'd call a policeman if you were naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh if she did we didn't take no notice. No, I don't think she'd do anything like that, she'd give it to you if you wanted it. Have do
ne with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Your home was rented and you thought quite a lot of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Do you remember as a child feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet, were you conscious of this as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, everybody was in the same boat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You didn't really notice it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
No, no, everybody - in fact as I say - it wouldn't matter how hard up mother and father were we mostly always had Sunday boots. I have been told that we were lucky to have that much. And - yes, y
es. And - I remember a girl saying to me once, your mother wash stockings? My mother never does. But my mother did, you know, there was that much, I don't know how it worked out but there it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You told me one or two incidents of your mother getting something from the Guardians?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How did they treat you in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Not very nice. Not very nice, of course you get the - we had the big loaves of bread and oatmeal and all likes of that. Not all that nice. And they didn't like you to have a lot of - home. I mean - I - think mother did }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1996598\charrsid13588098 pawn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
 a clock one time, 'cos - I mean - they - they said they did but I don't remember so much, I think we were shielded from the likes of that, mother and father shielded us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 When would you get this, when your father was out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes. And then he lost his }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1996598\charrsid13588098 vote}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098  that time, I know he was raving over that. 'Cos he did like his independence. He liked to chuck a job and get another one and all that kind of thing. Never minded having a change, but he didn't like losing his vote.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Can you remember anything else about how this system worked, The church obviously had a lot of authority?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I know my mother lost a baby one time, this is history - baby died in Guys and that was in 
Southwark, we lived in Bermondsey. Southwark wouldn't bury it because we lived in Bermondsey. Guys wouldn't bury it - Bermondsey wouldn't bury it because it was - died in - Southwark. Granny had had the experience with one of her men lodgers. She said, si
t down. The law of the land says that baby's got to be buried. Now leave off running about and don't let none of 'em worry you. Guys buried it. So it was done. Went down to - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName
}}Streatham{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Park{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, a nice little white coffin. I believe that was the last baby, I do
n't know, but I know everything in the garden was lovely once mother settled down, but she was going mad, you can imagine. Yes. 'Cos granny had had men lodgers, when she lost grandfather she was left with six of them, and she had men lodgers and they were
 working on the Thames Embankment. My mother remembered Cleopatra's Needle coming up the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Thames{\*\xmlclose} on the barge. 'Course I don't, that was before me, but - this man was killed on the 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Thames{\*\xmlclose} embankment, and Barts buried him. They couldn't find any relatives or 
anything about it so - granny had got a rough idea, or a good idea, and she told mother, she said, now settle down. That baby's got to be buried, it's the law of the land and - that'll be it. And Guys buried it. And of course we found afterwards that they
 have a funeral fund, or did have, I don't know if they still have. There's a lot of things that we don't know. It comes out by accident. My mother went through it one way and another you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 When there was someone in the district whom the people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they showed it?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
We have been told by some people that there was something called rough music, where a person was a wife beater or something unpleasant like that, the neighbours would go round and kick up a row of a night and frighten them out of the place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 It could be done, yes, it could be done by annoyance and that but I don't know that it was done as far as we were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1996598\charrsid13588098 concerned}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 . We were all fairly comfortable round about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Were you given any lessons by your parents or anyone before you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well of course as I said the old man'd lay the law down and tell us what to do and what not to do and - what he thought. They used to argue about religion.
 'Cos mother's father was a Unitarian, he knew all the old testament, he didn't believe in the new testament, of course father was Church of England, been to church school and all, 'course they used to argue about that. Mother had the old testament right 
at her fingers ends, but not the new. That's the only thing, we used to get that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 About five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you go for a whole day or just a half day when you started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 All day. I'm pretty sure, that I can't swear to but pretty sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What were the hours of school then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Nine 'til - four or half past. Or nine 'til twelve and then - two to four or half past, I don't remember exactly. Two to half past four I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What kind of a school was this, was this a board school or a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes, no, board school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Was it girls and boys mixed or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No. No, girls half and boys half. We all went to the same school. All - you know, the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How long did it take you to get there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh, not five or ten minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Was this walking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Oh yes, quite - quite close.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did anyone go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no. Oh no, as soon as you went you went. Take one another I suppose I don't - mother would go with you and book
 you in but after that we - fought our own battles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Where did you have your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well - if there was any at home we'd have it, if not we'd have school dinners.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did they have school dinners then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes, yes, we used to go to S
haftesbury Hall at - laid off the Borough. Run by the Shaftesbury people, used to go there, get tickets and go there for our meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How much were they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Not much - if anything. I don't remember. Not much. Yes. No, I think when it was necessary I
 think it was free, I don't know, I think it was. We didn't mind anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What sort of meals, were they good meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 As far as I know, I'm still here, don't ask me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Were they a cooked meal or were they just soup?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no, they were cooked
, they were cooked meals. Oh, soup kitchens, they had one in Snowsfields where we used to take a basin and get a basin and get a basin of soup. That was all free or a penny or tuppence, it wasn't much anyway. And they used to dish that out of a big copper
,
 like you boiled the clothes in. Oh yes, you could always go and get a bowl of soup. Oh yes, you could always keep - that's one thing about Bermondsey, you could always keep living, there was plenty of food and - you know - bits - somewhere to go. Somewhe
re you could get something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Quite a few charities to help people were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Oh yes, yes. And - factories - as I said there was the skin market you could get the bullocks cheek and likes of that very cheap, just over {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}London{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Bridge{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} there was Leadenhall Market. Go over there in the afternoons, 'cos there was no fridges then so the fish that was left - you could get a bagful for threepence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 This is what you mean by your strata of the working class living better than the artisans?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes, abso
lutely. Absolutely because perhaps we'd get the best of fish, where they'd be buying the cheapest. See? And it was the same Saturday afternoons, there was a big fruit shop there, we could go and get lovely peaches and pears and that sort of thing that you
 
definitely couldn't buy by the pound - or you couldn't buy anyway. But if they were the least little bit bruised, well you got a bagful as I say for a couple of coppers. And the best. And - you know, you could have a - eat it 'til it was gone, you know, h
ave a real good feed of it, it wasn't a case of eking it out like the boy did his manners, we just - had it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What did you think of school on the whole?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I didn't mind it. Didn't mind school at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 T
hey were very very good. Very good. Very particular. We all had to be just - 'course that's another thing with the better class school. We had to be clean. Hairs and that were all - supervised, yes, things like that. You'd never see us lot going to school
 anyhow, we were always tidy.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did they emphasise things like manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Oh yes. Yes, well you can guess that with yes ma'am and no ma'am and - if you please ma'am. I remember her standing over me to make me say, if you please. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes, we had to talk plain. Yes. Oh yes, we had to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well I suppose - if we got the cane the names went down in the punishment book, that was worse than having the cane really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 They used to cane the girls as well as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What sort of offences would you get the cane for, would it have to be very serious?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well I suppose it would, I don't think we got it for noth
ing sort of thing, in fact I don't remember ever having it. Our headmistress was a finicky with regard to keeping the place clean and tidy. She came in one day - rucked us, oh - that bit of paper had been on the stairs so many days and we'd all been up an
d down and we'd all done this and that bit of paper was still there and oh dear oh dear, thought she'd never leave off. Very fussy she was with things like this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What sort of punishments did they give you if they didn't use the cane very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh I suppose we had to stay in and write lines, the usual.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 To a certain extent, yes. Not an awful lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did they visit the school or meet the teachers or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh they came up now and again, mother did, I don't remember father going unless he went for Harry, he wouldn't come for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did the other children come from similar type homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes. Much the same, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No - I don't think ours did. No, I don't think ours did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Were there any gangs or groups in the school? Or any children left out of things? Did you go on to another school afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, no, stayed there. Stayed right there 'til fourteen, right the way through. We all three did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Would you have stayed any longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well that's hard to say, you didn't get the opportunity so that was that. No, I don't think so,
 you were all anxious to get away out of it weren't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you attend any part time education afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I went to evening classes a few times but only for first aid and that's about - and I didn't like it so I soon got tired of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I don't think so really and truly. No I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Do you think you benefited at all from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh certainly, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 While you were at school did you have any part time jobs or any means or earning a little regular money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no. No. That's one thing the old man would not have. Oh no, no, no - no children at work, no, and neither did }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1996598\charrsid13588098 money}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 . My grandsons have, but not my children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What was your first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Went to service didn't I, chucked out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You went into service at fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How did you get this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 From school. Somebody recommended me. That was that. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How long were you in service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Until I was about - well 'til the war broke out, so you can reckon that out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You went into service, how long were you in your first position?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Four or five years, quite a long time. Yes, quite a long time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Now how many servants were there there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Only me. The missus used to do the cooking, I only done the work. Got the veg ready for her. We had a woman came in and done the washing.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you go away from home to this place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes, I slept in, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Whereabouts, was this far from your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Only about Balham. Tram ride. It was like going out to the country, but still.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Did you feel that the mistress was interested in you as a person at all, did she look after you, give you any moral guidance or things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, all she done was - ruck 
when the National Health came along at that time, of course that was a terrible thing. Every single girl was going to have a baby, you were all being encouraged to do everything you shouldn't. Oh no, you didn't get any moral guidance, you only got rucked.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Where did you sleep and eat in this house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I had my own room and ate in the kitchen, they had their dining room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 So you didn't eat with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no. No. 'Course that was only guiver, but still.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh all the hours Gold Almighty sent, if they wanted you up in the middle of the night they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You didn't have any set hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no. Nobody had set hours in service in those days. You were lucky if you got half a day a week and then you had to do t
he work and wash up lunch things before you went, that made it 'ere two or three o'clock.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Sunday about once a month. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you get any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No. No, I was - the second job I had - I asked about a h
oliday. And she said I could have a holiday in the September. I told my mother - or my father. He said, 're, you're going to be home for Christmas. So when I told her that she turned nasty and I turned nasty, I turned that job in. I didn't stay there very
 long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How much were you paid on this first job? You were there about five years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Yes. Started at two bob I think and finished up about - see two bob was about ten pound a year, ten, twelve pound a year and finished up about sixteen, eighteen pound a year, not a lot. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you feel that it was a fair wage at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 It was. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you give any of this money to your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No. No. Not - not definite, if I thought I would I did and if I didn't I didn't. 'Cos mother
 used to say, well you don't take anything out. That was that. But if I - when I was going in - perhaps I'd take a cake or something in for tea but nothing - 'course I kept myself in clothes, which you had to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh all right, I never had any -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How did you feel about the work, did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I don't mind housework. I don't mind housework at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did the job alter your attitude to school in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you feel at ease with the members of the family while you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes, I was always as good as the next one. If they started anything they got answer.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you feel homesick?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh first go off, yes, but you get over that don't you, you had to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you feel lonely, being the only servant in the place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well no, give me a book and I could forget everything, I can now. Sometimes people say here, 'cos I'm up this end but I stay up this end, I've always got a book or a paper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Was there anything you particularly liked or disliked about that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well - the old lady, she was very old, that's why they had me really as much companion for her, and - she'd got very conservative ideas and she was a bit - awkward, I suppose 
I was as well. She'd been in service with - titled people, and she thought it was very marvelous, if she met them out they'd shake hands with her. 'Course I couldn't see that. That didn't strike on my account. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about the washing, was that sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
No, a woman came in and done that. And - I think - I don't know whether I done the ironing or - or they done it between them. Think I done some of it, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Who mended the clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh I don't a lot of darning, I liked darning, I still do. But - their own they done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You said the woman of the house did the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. That's where I first found that a joint lasted all the week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did they have any children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, no. No, they were grown up, they was - the o
ld lady was very old and the other two - they were at work, they were schoolteachers. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How many were there in the household?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Only three. Two daughters and the mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Where did they eat their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 In the dining room, they had dining room, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What cooking equipment was there in the house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh was a kitchen range and the gas stove. 'Cos that was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Would they all have breakfast together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, I think they had it - had theirs and went out and - perhaps I had mi
ne with the old lady, I don't remember, I know I used to have lunch with her, elevenses we used to have together. But about breakfast, I've been asleep since then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What did they have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh - I think eggs and bacon, porridge, whatever was going. Yes, quite ordinary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did they do any jam making or bottling or beer making or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Not beer making. I think they made a little bit - yes, they did make jam, they had a big copper thing, but they used to do that, not me.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did they grow any fruit or vegetables at this house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, it wasn't big enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did they keep any livestock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No. Only one cat. As I say I don't like cats. But still I tolerate - I'm not cruel to anything, but - I don't like cats. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How many times a week was meat eaten at this place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh every day. Every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no, nobody had it in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you have the same food as them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you ever used to go out with the family at weekends or Bank Holidays or anything like this, did they ever take you out at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
No, they used to take the old lady out in a bath chair, but I never went with them. I'd go out and do the shopping, get round the shops, stay as long as I liked, I wasn't timed about you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did they think it wrong to work or play on a Sunday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well of course if they wanted you to work you worked. We didn't do an awful lot Sundays though, they were on the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did they go to church or chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes. They went to church. They used to - spell each other of to cook the Sunday lunch, go to church. And mostly always I went.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you used to go with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Or to the same church, I don't know that I sat with them, I - perhap
s I didn't want to. I don't know, I might have done with the young one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Was grace said at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No. Not with me, I don't know what they done in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did they take any interest in politics do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, I don't think they did, I - if they did they were the opposite to me so of course we didn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What were their interests, did they have any interests outside the home at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well they went in for - amateur dramatics, yes, they done quite a lot of that. They used to give 
me tickets - there was a - place in the Camberwell New Road, it's not - where Steele Griffiths' is now there used to be a theatre there but - not there any more. They used to have the - plays and that there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did they do any work for charities or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
No. No. They - they had as much as they could do, they were schoolteachers, time they came home, marked their books and etcetera etcetera - one or two evenings out that was - they had their lot didn't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did they have any friends or people call round, did they do much entertaining?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Do you think that they were content with their station in life or do you think they would have liked to have been higher up the social scale?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I think they were quite - contented with it. Yes. I think so. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What did you think of them and their way of living?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well I think I preferred our own way of going on. Yes, I think I - you know, our own way, I - this - so much and no more and all that kind of thing, too regulated for me, I - I was all right while I was there but I wouldn't liked to have led that life.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You felt they were too careful somehow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did their manners and general behaviour seem very much different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no, no, No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You went to another one in Lawn Road, Brixton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Brixton. Yes. I wasn't there so very long. They were all grown up, there was a son and a daughter. Son got married. The daughter was - nursing at - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Evelina{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Hospital{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. Very lovely girl she was. Red hair. She wanted to be a matron, I don't know whether she got that far, but - it's all right but it just wasn't all right, because I know me.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you go anywhere from that one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No. No. I packed up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Then you went as a waitress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You were a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12072762\charrsid13588098 waitress}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098  then until the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 'Til the war or just before the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How much did you used to get as a waitress in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Generally thirteen shillings. I do remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about tips?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Tips? Not many, Everybody was in the same boat weren't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How did you get this waitressing job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
I just - I think we - through the Labour Exchange, where the Labour Exchange is up - either there or through the papers or something. It was always paper - always jobs to be got.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What hours did you work at this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I think from about eight 'til six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about Saturdays and Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Didn't work Sundays, I know the old man wouldn't have that. I suppose lunch time Saturday, I don't - yes, it w
as lunch time because it was - over in the City. Closed - closed lunch time Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you have holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No. Nobody got paid for holidays. Don't ask silly questions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you feel this was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 It had to be, yes, you got a standard wage, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you go back to living at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you give any of this money to your mother then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I suppose I did, I don't - couldn't tell you exactly. 'Cos we - that included meals, the thirteen sh
illings included meals there. But again you didn't take much out and my mother was reasonable. You don't take much out you don't bring much in, that's that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 So most of that would have been for yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes, it would have been mine, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How did you get on with the people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 All right. - As I say, we used to spit fire and get over it, that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How did you get on with your employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh - well, of course we had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12072762\charrsid13588098 manageress\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 , they were all right. They were only the same as us. Meet them halfway and you're all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How did you feel about this work as compared with your domestic service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 As a waitress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well of course you had got more freedom, you - you didn't get called in the 
night if anybody was ill or anything. When you were finished you were finished. And - when you had your slack times on the job - you were all slack together. See? I mean - after you finished your lunches you were slack then until the - afternoon teas came
 on, you got more freedom didn't you. Oh yes, much better. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Then when the war started you went on war work, you started off on gas masks, how much a week was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I think it was a pound a week, pound or twenty-five - was the - scale then.
 'Course that was the first start of paying labour money, we never had labour cards 'til then. And then of course - down the Arsenal I know it was twenty-five and then we got the bonus - on top you see. And I hadn't been there very long before I got }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12072762\charrsid13588098 overlookers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098  job. And I got eight shillings a week - plus bonus, more than they did. More than - yes, I was doing all right.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How long were you making gas masks before you changed over?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I should think - I don't know - six to twelve months. Yes, it would
n't have been very long, no, - no, because I was having a fight with me father wasn't I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What exactly did you do in the gas mask work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Gas masks? We were tightening up the eye pieces. As they came through they had to be tightened up and tested a
nd passed. You see. We tightened them up and then there was somebody at the end tested them. That's the job my sister got after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Do you remember the hours on this job, were they longer than the waitressing or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, about the same, I think it was about eight 'til six or eight 'til - yes, it would be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What did you do when you went down the Arsenal, what was your job there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well I - we were in cordite, tidying up the cordite to go in the shell cases. And they were - danger buildings, w
e got extra money for that. 'Course we were three miles from the main gate but - you took it in your stride, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You used to have to walk that did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes, had to walk that and change out from your own clothes into fireproof clothes. No hairp
ins or - bootlaces or anything, we had wooden - shoes, put together with studs, you know, wooden studs. And the windows were all on slots. No - no nails, No friction at all, and it was built up on a platform as high as that from the ground. You walked on 
p
latforms. You didn't realize you know - that it was - you were anyway. And - I had the first aid girl on my shop. Don't know what good she was, but she was on the book anyway, and if there was any trouble she was out and you never knew when she was coming
 
back, and she used to have screaming hysterics. And this night - we never knew when - when they were testing the guns the windows used to all rattle and this night the window came in. I caught sight of her quick. She was just getting ready to have a screa
m
ing set up. And then of course you'd have all the floor walkers, everybody in. I said, you do. I said, now you scream. My name's Warwick, you'll get that fire bucket clean over you. They said, Miss Warwick, you cured her. She never done it no more to me. 
Oh, my God she used to scream. And yet she had the first aid job.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you do shift work there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes, fortnight days, fortnight nights. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You say you had to walk three miles, was this before you clocked on or after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes, before yo
u clocked, and change and all before you clocked on. Oh yes. That's what the old man was rucking me for wasn't he. 'Cos he done it during the Boer War. Still we done it. You made up your mind you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What were the hours there at Woolwich?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Not too bad I don't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 They were a bit better than the gas masks were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well - ordinary anyway. We done thirteen nights. Think it was thirteen nights a fortnight, I suppose twelve or so days, I can't tell you, I know we changed once a fortnight. It was all right, I enjoyed myself anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How long were you there before you became an overlooker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Not too long. Not too long at all, I often wondered whether Uncle Joe did have any influence, I don't know of course. I was tapped on the sh
oulder told that I'd got to take over the job - the shop next door. I said, I don't want it. They said, you either take it or you get the sack, and that meant six weeks out of work. So of course there was nothing to do but take it. But I didn't really and
 truly want it. Still we done all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Would you have preferred any other type of occupation in your life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well I would rather have been apprenticed to a - a trade, because you can always go back to those. But then you didn't do - what was the 
use of - my mother thought service was the best that time, they thought you know -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Was there any trade you thought you fancied particularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, not particularly, I didn't know at that time. They wanted my mother to take us in with her. The for
ewoman said to her, bring your Carrie in. Mother said, no. No, she said, been good enough for you all these years. But of course - I woke up then. They were piecework. But they put in far more work than they done. It's a wonder that the firms didn't go br
oke. Must have been very very - you know, must have done because - and of course she brought us up that we wouldn't dare tell lies or say anything and she was doing it all herself wasn't she. We didn't know then. But - she wouldn't take us in with her.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you ever belong to any trade union or professional organisation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Not 'til later, no, not - not when we were single. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Have you been in any at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well I - as I say, I did belong to the - Public Employees when I worked at East Dulwich.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you take part in any of the activities of the union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Not a lot, they gave me the offer once or twice but I couldn't, I was tied - the children, I just didn't - and mother and father were with me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests or different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well as far as we were concerned of course the - sisters and nurses, they were all supposed to be - just that bit superior and - we helped - we held our own. 'Cos us cleaners, we could give them a back answer where the nurses couldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you feel that there was a division of interest among the workers themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no. No. No, we didn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you feel that there was any great division between trained craftsmen and other workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well of
 course the cooks were that much - they got more money for one thing and they were - boss of their own domains like, we weren't, we had to - fall in with them, but - otherwise there wasn't a lot in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No I don't think so. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you continue to live at home after you left school, up until the time you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes. Never thought of anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 While you were in service you still used to go back home on your off time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did starting full time work change the relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, I don't think so. No I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How about with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, we all - all done our own jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You didn't feel any more independent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no, no, we - no, no, we went on just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you spend your Sunday any differently, did you still go to church and chapel, or not so much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Might not have gone so much but - I don't know that there was a lot of difference. No. Don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you start to take an interest in politics at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well, no, only that - you heard the arguments, you didn't take any interest in it, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you vote at all, you say you started voting as soon as you could, you took an interest in political ideas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well - just a little bit, yes, but only as I say because it was rubbed into you. Wasn't that you properly understood what they were talking about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What were your views at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well of course I was in with my father wasn't I. I mean, you thought the money was all in - the hands of too few people that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you ever take part in any political activity apart from voting? How about
 your spare time while you were living at home, while you were at school you used to go to the music hall occasionally with your parents?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes, well we carried on the same, only that we went by ourselves with our own friends. We - made our own fri
ends, but we still didn't take anybody indoors much, not a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Where did you meet these new friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well just round about where we lived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 They were more or less people you'd gone to school with were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 YES. Yes. YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you make any totally new friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Not a lot, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Mainly ones you'd grown up with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What sort of things would you go to in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well as I say, we had the Band of Hope, the girls clubs, the - Girls Friendly Society, that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I didn't ask you about the activities did I?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well there wasn't a lot in it as far as I know, we - use to play games, you know, table games - and that. Wasn't a lot in it, it was only just passing the time away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you ever bring friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No. Very seldom. Very very seldom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How did you meet these new friends, nowadays people go to coffee bars and these places what did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, I don't know, we never seemed to want to, we were quite
 - don't know whether we were extraordinary docile or what but - we didn't seem to do - or want to do half the things that - we didn't go to dances or anything. Could have done but we just didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did your parents meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes, we all met. Yes, there was no - bar up of anything or anybody.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did they expect to know where you were when you went out still?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well we used to give them an idea where we were going but - they weren't too fussy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you have to be back by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well I think we done that for our own sakes, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You don't think it's particularly important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, no, I don't think it is. I wasn't with mine either so I mean you carry on pretty well the same don't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You spent several years in service before living back at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Were you allowed to take friends back to the house there or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I never did. No, I never did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you still go to the cinema in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Not a lot, I didn't like it very much. I didn't like it very much.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
I think what I was keen to get quite clear in my mind was where you were, what job you were doing when the war actually started, the first world war, were you in service then when the war actually began?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
I was - but I didn't stay, I was with Germans and I wasn't there long, that was over Stamford Hill, and they - interned one or two of them and I sort of turned Charlie and packed in. Stupid I - I can realize now, but - the fact that they were 
interned, they were all right, I should have stayed, but there you are, you do these things don't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Was it a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes. A - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Who did they intern then, the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12072762\charrsid13588098 whole family}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, it was - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12072762\charrsid13588098 niece}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098  or nephew or something of that - it was a big bakers shop, but I was up in the house, I wasn't in the shop. And they were really good people, 'course I can see it now can't I?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 So that was the job you had after you'd been in Balham was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Balham was the one that you went to after the boarding house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 And that was where they expected you to keep carting the children up and down stairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Have you any idea how long you were in the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Not so very long,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12072762\charrsid13588098  because I got tonsillitis}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098  myself, and I didn't go back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Would that have been less than a year then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes, I should think so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Perhaps six months?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes, something like that, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Not that long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No. And that was the only place as far as I can remember where I had boots to clean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Was it there you had to iron the shoelaces?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, I - I've never ironed -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You were talking about Margaret Powell and you said there was something she had to do and you remembered you'd had to do the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What was it? No, it wasn't - no, we didn't do that far. No, I've never done that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Or ironing the newspaper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Shining under the - arch of the shoes. Yes. Shining under the arch of the shoes. And never so disgusted in my life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How many children did they have that family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
There was - three, two boys and a - no, two girls and a - three - three girls. Three girls. The boy - they - I didn't see him, he was in school in Germany. The boy was. I didn't see him at all, not the
 boy. No, there was three little girls. Well - the two were big girls, they were going to secondary school. They went to a convent school although they were protestants. But they reckoned it was a better education.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You left there with tonsillitis, were you at home for quite a long time before you got another job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 A - few weeks I expect. Not too long. Nobody kept you for nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How did you find the job in Stamford Hill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Probably answered an advertisement. 'Cos we - we had a code betwe
en ourselves that you never went to work for anybody church or chapel people because we didn't get much money anyway but you got less with those. Yes. They'd got the name - the church and chapel people did not pay wages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 When you went for an interview how could you find out if the people were church or chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well you didn't go - you didn't - get transferred for - you answered a - newspaper - and I mean with business people and that you generally find out, it comes along, you don't ask those questions but - it - you realize.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 If you found they were very ardent church or chapel you mean you wouldn't have taken the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well, not unless they were going to pay all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 They were the stingiest were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 They were. They'd got the name of it anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 In the job in Balham were you still the only servant in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 And the same at Stamford Hill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. No, we had help there. I can't re - think there was a cook. I think there was three or four of us 
there, and - there was a nursery maid there, they had a couple of children, there was a nursery maid because - they were business people, just ordinary business people, but this nursery girl had been in a big house, and she was telling her how to dress he
r
 kids. Going to the shops in the West End and - what to get and that. And - they were - they didn't grudge anything like that, there was plenty of money there, but they just didn't have the - what would you call it - the idea of - being just that much ove
r. The nurse -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 They didn't mind her telling them what to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No. No. No, they were quite - quite clever to be as good as - everybody else. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How long were you in that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Not very long, as I say, I gave it up, the war broke out and
 - I just told them I didn't feel like working for them, stupid but still, there you are, you do these things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 And then you went straight into munitions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Then a little time as a waitress?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. No, as a waitress first. Yes. And then - munitions, forgot that one and went - down the Arsenal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You did mention you thought you were a waitress in between the two bite of war work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, I may have been but not a lot. No, I think - it - it's as well just to say the once. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 But after the war you had that job where you were sort of a housemaid were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Would you have called yourself a housemaid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well - yes. Well ward maid than. You were all classed alike. Yes. And they - allotted your - you ei
ther went in the nurses home or the wards - according. What }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12072762\charrsid13588098 turned up}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 But that was after the war had ended?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Do you have quite a clear recollection of that, you told me quite a few things about it last time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes. Oh yes
, yes. Well of course there was more freedom there than there was in a private house. There was more of us and - with regard to nurses and sisters of course you could - sort of speak and that and I had one or two nurses that were very kind to me. They tol
d
 me if anything - if I wanted a sanitary towel or anything I could go to their drawers and get it and like that, well you couldn't do that in service. See? And they were very good the girls up there were. And the part of the nurses home where I was - was 
q
uite near the Roman Catholic church, and a couple of these girls were Roman Catholics and they used to dodge down the fire escape and go into church and come back again quickly you see, it - we were all very happy up there really. It was an old type - it'
s - I think it's all bombed now up there, but it was quite - and they weren't such nice rooms as in the ordinary nurses home. But they were very happy up there. You know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you share a room there or did you have your own room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I think we had cu
bicles, with just curtains in the front. Yes. We had our own cubicle but there was - curtains in the fronts. Up there. And where these nurses were was much the same, we were one half and they come the other side. Theirs was much the same as ours.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 When you were in that job in Stamford Hill, what were you called there, what was your title as it were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh just housemaid wasn't it? Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you get better money each time you moved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I think so, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 It was sort of promotion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes, if it was only half a crown a week it was a bit you know or - perhaps two shillings a week. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Were you always called just Carris?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 And you always called them madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You were never in the kind of job where you were on a more equal footing with people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Can you think of anything particularly that stands out in your mind about the job in Balham, or the job in Stamford Hill? Can you think of anything you particularly remember th
at was interesting about those jobs? Which of all the jobs in service do you think you have the clearest recollection of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well I think the one at Brixton where the men and that were. She was the hardest and I was there the longest. I think that was the -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 The one you remember most of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Yes. Yes. That's the one - I - I resented a lot of it there, cleaning steps in cold water and all that sort of thing, I really resented that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You also seem to remember quite a lot about the one with the schoolteachers too?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Perhaps because it was your first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes. And I was more friendly with them of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 And with the old mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You were more like a companion to her weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Were you with the schoolteachers a shorter time do you think that the Brixton job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Yes, I think so, because the old lady did get on me nerves, and they gave in to me. They gave in to me, or at least they gave in to my mother, they said yes, she wanted some putting up with.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Was the job that you had after you left the lady who was a schoolteacher at your school that you worked for, I believe you went to a job in Long Road, Brixton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I wondered if you could tell me who your employers were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Yes, well it was a Mrs - Maddison, and she was running - more or less a boarding house, they were - men - working in offices and that, they had their own rooms, and she used to go - breakfast and evening meal, an
d Sunday's meals for them. And - she had a woman in once a week that used to do the washing, I think I had to do the ironing but I don't know, we done that between us I suppose. But - she was very very hard to work for, very hard, and yet - and she was th
e
 one that cooked me for a reference. She caught me - lighting a - reading the paper before I lit the fire, and she used to catch me reading and that, and when it came - I'd worked for her for three years before I left. See - I hadn't had a holiday up 'til
 
then, and she offered me to go away in September. I suppose I caught me father on the wrong foot, he said, do you want to be home again for Christmas, he says, that's too late to go away in the year. So I went back and told her and gave her a month's noti
c
e, and - she just put that I was - not dishonest, untrustworthy. See? Well then I had to - go back to the schoolteachers, and - work the reference from there again, you know what I mean, because they were shocking with reference those days. And so unneces
sary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did the schoolteachers give you another fresh reference then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes, I think they did, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You explained to them did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes, ex - yes, and I went to work-for some friends of theirs, at Balham, I - that's where they had the 
children. Where I used to carry the children up to bed when they weren't well and when I wasn't well myself they sent me home. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 But when she put that you were untrustworthy, did you question that at all, did you say anything to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I t
hink my mother and father had a go at her. Because there'd been a bit of trouble - she had some Australians staying there at one time, and the - lad, he was about - teenager, he came up to my room one night and of course I told him where to get off, and t
h
at was another grievance I had, the man in the next room to me - could tell her what time I put my light out or what I'd been doing in there, and yet he didn't hear this. And I had shouted at that boy. And I told her the next morning, the father was suppo
sed to be very upset, it was all put - you know, paid to, and my mother went for her over that. But - nothing came of it, I mean - well there was no need for anything to come of it, he - he just went and that was that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Do you think she gave her son a row?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Probably did. Well he - these were Australians, they weren't her own people. Boys - yes, staying there you see. See they weren't her own people. No, they were staying there. I think his - it was his father and mother and this boy. I think the - 
the mother and father went for him, I don't know, but anyway of course they were only there temporary and they went away and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 He didn't bother you any more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 It must have been rather upsetting for you away from home like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
I don't know, I must have been very placid I think somehow or other, I didn't seem to get hysterical or anything. 'Cos they didn't - nobody else in the house knew, even the man in the next room - said he didn't know. Can't believe that myself, I've always
 had me doubts with that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 He used to sort of report on you did he, this man in the next room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Yes. Oh yes, he was quite good at that. Especially if I had the light on too late or what not he'd tell her. He was horrible. He was horrible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 And it was all men lodging there was it, except for these Australians?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 That's right, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 They were the only sort of family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes. Yes, there was a man in the next room, and in the big back room, the back - the back rooms come b
igger than the front, there was two in the front, you know, a big room and a small room, I had a small one, and then the back room - was a policeman in that room. And then she had the room under him. I don't know who was in the other two rooms. I don't kn
o
w who - I think one was kept for the daughter, she was a nurse at - Evelina hospital, she was training for a nurse, well she had such a bad time in the hospital, washing in cold water and - no convenience and of course I got the backlash of that. Margaret
 
had to put up with this and Margaret had to put up - with the other so of course I did didn't I, and I didn't have sense enough to - but there, things were a lot different sixty, seventy years ago to what they are - sixty years ago to what they ware now. 
We had to put up with it, mothers and fathers backed those people, they didn't back us.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I wondered if it worried your mother at all that you were in the house with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12072762\charrsid13588098 all these}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098  single men?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well - I don't think it did, I don't think - she sort of ho
ped for the best and - that was that. And of course they were - they were really decent men, they weren't bad men, you know, they were really decent working men. Well - of - clerks and that sort of thing, they weren't - flash - show offs. No, they were re
a
lly decent working men, that there was - I wasn't frightened of them. No, I wasn't frightened of them even if they came up and I was doing their rooms, which I didn't, they - they were always at work when they were being done. But I wasn't frightened of t
hem at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did they give you little tips or presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No. No. No, you don't get anything of that in those days. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 When they left they wouldn't give you a present?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, well they were there all the time, they were still there when I left. They'd been there all the time before me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 They didn't have a rapid turnover there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no, no, that was it you see - had they had have - these Australians were the only strangers we had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 They were there when you came and there when you left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes, the others were, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How long were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Three years altogether. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 She had very permanent people there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 But she should not have cooked me for reference, but there you are, they did in those days. You sort of 
- oh you were frightened of your own life. It is,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14181650\charrsid13588098  is}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098  terrible. Especially when you think what they get away with now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 And the way we had to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 And that's the way they paid you for all that hard work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Very little. Very little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What sort of time in the morning did you have to get up there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
You had to be down by seven anyway. And get things straightened up by the time she come down to cook their breakfast. She used to do all the cooking mind you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You didn't have to make any tea for them in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
No. No, I didn't do any of that sort of thing. I never went up to their rooms, hardly ever while they were in it. Anything like that she done herself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Would you have to blacklead the grate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes, yes, you had to blacklead grates, clean steps and in cold water in the winter. It was terrible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did she have a hot water system at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No. No. There was a little tank - the side of the kitchen range, and she caught me once draining that out one morning an
d she went for me. Still I used to dodge her, I don't mind telling you, she didn't get it all her own way. No. 'Cos it may have been things like that that I was more or less frightened to fight her too much because I didn't know what else she'd dig up, 'c
os once - you know, they dig it up and dig it up don't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 When she made breakfast what would you do after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well wash up and do what - you know, tidy up the kitchen, do the veg ready -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you wash up together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no, I done all that. I done all that out in the - yes, all that out in the kitchen, not a lot of convenience.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you have hot water for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well yes, kettles of water. Kettles of water. Oh yes, always soda, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Hard on the hands wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well they said so and yet it didn't affect mine, but I've got a sweaty kind of a hand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You've got most skin really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 So perhaps you didn't dry so much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No. No. I - I never had them filthy. No, my hands were never filthy. And - a
nd even now they don't you know, whatever I'm doing I don't get -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Cracked and dirty hands?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
No. No. And my mother was a bit fussy over hers, I think she used to grease them and keep them, you know, it sort of burns - born in you isn't it that sort of thing. Father was always proud of his fingernails and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 He kept his hands nice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 When you'd done the breakfast things what was your next job of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well I should think - doing the kitchen - we had mid
day lunch but she used to do an evening meal for the - others, and a - that would mean getting veg and that ready but I suppose I would do that more in the afternoon, I forget really. Of course steps and passage - was probably done while they were having 
b
reakfast, then go out and clear all up out there - of course dining room was done before breakfast, first thing in the morning that was done and got ready for them. And then there was a - what they called a drawing room at the back, parlour - and - then g
radually go up and do different rooms, different days, 'cos the big staircase - bathroom, etcetera. I wasn't allowed to have a bath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You couldn't use the bathroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No. No. It wasn't allowed. And - of course there was no central heating then, she 
had a gas burner under the bath that they used to light up to heat the water, but I wasn't allowed to do that, I had to manage with a - kettle of water upstairs. Best way you can, yes. Well of course we done that in me own home so - wasn't much odds.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 But still it seems rotten to have a bathroom and not to be able to use it doesn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Yes. Yes, but there you are, that's the way things went in those days. The class distinction was dreadful. Dreadful. It's hard to - realize. Is this thing still on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you have lunch with her or did you eat on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
No, I had mine out in the kitchen, I think she used to have hers on the tray in the - dining room, and she used to have a sleep in the afternoon on the couch in the dining room, 'cos whil
e she was there I had to be upstairs - doing the rooms or - changing frock and that ready for the - afternoon and evening. Opening doors etcetera.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did she have any callers in the afternoon that you had to make tea for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, I don't think she had a - no, I don't think so, I don't remember that part of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Why do you think she made you change your clothes then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well I suppose just to - for neighbours really and truly you know, just for - as I say, people round about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 For show sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Yes. Yes, that's all life was wasn't it. Make believe. 'Cos she was a widow you see and she was - making a living for herself and the daughter, the sons were married, they used to come - weekends mostly, one son used to come every Sunday dinn
ertime when he come out of church, I think he was a sidesman or something, I didn't like him. But that didn't matter. And he - only had to just let him in and that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 But basically it was just her living alone then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes. And the daughter when she was off duty from - Evelina.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How did the daughter treat you, was she full of class distinction too in her way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 In her way, yes. Yes. Yes, she was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you have to call her Miss and that sort of thing?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes, Miss Margaret. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What about the widow, what did you call her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Ma'am. Yes, always ma'am.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 And she called you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Carrie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 You didn't call her Mrs or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh no, no, oh my dear. Oh my dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did they all call you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12072762\charrsid13588098 C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 arrie, all the men who lived there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 And you called them Mr?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes. Only remember one name and that was the man that had the room next to me, Mr Openshaw. That's the only name I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 When they had their dinner in the evening did she sit and eat with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
I think she must have done. Yes, 'cos she would have served and - been there with them, yes, she would have served and been there with them and then of course I had to clear all that away and see to it again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What time did they have that meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I should think about six or seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 When they got back from work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes, six or seven, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Hours were that bit longer then weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you have to hand round vegetables and sort of wait at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No. Not as far as I remember there. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 She would have looked after that side of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Mm. Yes. Yes. And they were - ordinary enough to - reach and get themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Then you cleared all that away, then did you have anything else to do after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well of course there was always a bit of something, clearing up or cleaning silver or something, there was mostly always something in the evenings, until it was bedtime about nine or ten o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 A very long day wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 It was a very very long day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Was there any time when you could sit, put your feet up or just sit and read a book during the day, official time I mean?
