\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes, it is when you think about it, yes. Of course you didn't realize it then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Well lots of other people were in the same boat weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes. Everybody was in the same boat. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Then you left her and she gave you this rotten reference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Then I went over to Balham where those kids were. Those four children there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 So you had about four years with the schoolteachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 About three years with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 So by that time you'd have been about twenty-one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 The war would have been on then wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Getting on, I left then. That's when I gave up service. During the war, the early part of the war, that's when I fought me father. 'Cos I wanted to go down the Arsenal and he sai
d, you don't. He worked there during the Boer War, and - I got another job - on munitions on - this was another bit of wangling - gas masks, and you weren't allowed to leave one munitions and go to another. See? So - to get down the Arsenal, I had to forg
et gas masks, and give a previous reference, and I got down there. And I was there - for the rest of the war.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 When the war ended you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I was still there, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 How did you get the previous reference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I think in between t
imes I'd worked for - at the ABC as a waitress, only for a few weeks. Yes, only for a few weeks but that was near enough, that I could say I'd worked there - and went from there - there. They weren't so particular for references, they went back - for your
 own pedigree. Your mother and father, where they went to school, where you were born, all the pedigree to get into munitions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 For security reasons I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 It was, yes, it was - 'course I was down on danger buildings - see? And that's why my f
ather didn't want me to go, he'd worked during the Boer War and he said you'd got three miles to walk before you get - when you get inside the gate, you've got three miles to walk before you book on, but still the more - more - opposition anybody gives me
 
the closer I - stick, I'm just the same now, and of course I got the job, and I stayed. I hadn't been there so very long - there was a mix up with the bookings, we had two - I was on cordite, and we had two different size boxes, one used to hold I think f
i
fty odd and the other forty. Well I was pretty honest with my booking, and I got into a row, the woman in the next - shop, we worked on a combine, we all got the same wages all the shops that were working together got the same wages - they were booking in
 
more than they done, and they said they were earning our money, and I said, well - all I know, is, I said, we work all the time we're here, I was in charge by this time, I said, all I know is - I said, we work all the time we're here and what's going on I
 
do not know, and it turned out then she was booking them all as big boxes when they were - more or less all small. Was only a small amount but still it was enough - to get me into a row, and - you know, so - she got put off. I said I'd turn the job in and
 they said well if you do you'll get six weeks with no money, no labour money, no nothing, that's the way they punished us then, and - I was put in charge of the shop, actually - in charge of it. So we carried on from there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 What was your sort of title, were you called a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12072762\charrsid13588098 charge hand}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes. Overseer. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 And you got a bit extra money for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Yes, eight shillings a week. And a percentage of the bonus. We got that every so often. Bonus every so often. 'Course we never knew quite what we were getting. 'Cos the standard money then, even on munitions was only twenty-five. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 And you got another eight on top of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 But it was a lot better pay than service wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Oh yes. Yes. More freedom too. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Why do you think your father didn't want you to go into munitions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
Well I think he thought of the journey. 'Cos - he didn't believe in this traveling to work. He believe that - if you couldn't have a job next door to where you lived well you just
 didn't do it. You didn't do an hours traveling before you done a day's work, he reckoned that was - as bad as work, because he was a right rebel. But - however I got there and I - suited myself, and he done it all wrong during that war, he signed on for 
n
ational service, he was too old for the army, he signed on for national service, he's a very very good - blacksmith striker, and they put him in Dalton's - factory, you know, where they make the - what do you call it, not china - no, no, - that sort of th
ing -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Porcelain?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
No, no, they didn't call it that then. It'll - it'll come in a minute, anyway - they put him there and they - they broke up all the - crockery, and made - shell cases of it, and he was sharpening the tools for the girls to do the
 work. But I earnt more money than he did. You see? The girls were earning the money too, 'cos they were on - ammunition, but he was on national service, he got a flat rate. And - just one of those things, you sign on - thinking you're going to be clever 
and you're not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 He was caught out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Yes, he was very badly caught out there, very badly caught out because - he really was a good workman.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 That work in munitions, that was the first experience you'd had really of something like factory work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Factory work. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Did you come across and meet the sort of type of girl you hadn't associated much with before there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, I think a lot of us - 'cos it was new to everybody. It was new to everybody and I think a lot of us were all p
ractically in the same boat, and of course we were all young enough to - accommodate ourselves. And - we used to have one or two barnies but still we got over that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 I wondered if your father had felt that it might be a bit sort of rough for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 
No, I don't think that - no, no, it was the traveling he objected to, 'cos we had to get up to London Bridge station - and from there we had to get a train down to Plumstead, and - it was a journey, a long journey.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 And you had your fares?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 And fares, yes. Yes. But of course you took all that in your stride, you didn't - think too much about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16391728 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 Was there a trade union there at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14383286 CC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4403921\charrsid13588098 No, no, not then. No. No. No there was nothing of that in those days.
